{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019igXpdpsF9dgvuftbSbYUh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n     3→        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n     4→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     5→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     6→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\"\n     7→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     8→<h:head>\n     9→  <title><ui:insert name=\"title\">Title</ui:insert></title>\n    10→\n    11→  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" />\n    12→  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n    13→\n    14→  <h:outputStylesheet name=\"css/app.css\" />\n    15→\n    16→  <link rel=\"stylesheet\"\n    17→    href=\"//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.3.0/css/font-awesome.min.css\" />\n    18→</h:head>\n    19→\n    20→<h:body>\n    21→  <div class=\"ui-g full-page\">\n    22→    <!-- MENU -->\n    23→    <div class=\"ui-g-12 ui-md-2 side-panel\">\n    24→      <div class=\"ui-g-12 menu-container\">\n    25→        <h:form>\n    26→          <h:graphicImage value=\"#{resource['/images/CTlogobadge128.png']}\"\n    27→            class=\"side-panel-img\" alt=\"Cargo Tracker logo badge\" />\n    28→          <p:menu>\n    29→            <p:menuitem value=\"Dashboard\"\n    30→              url=\"#{request.contextPath}/admin/dashboard.xhtml\" />\n    31→            <p:menuitem value=\"Book\" action=\"booking\" />\n    32→            <p:menuitem value=\"Track\"\n    33→              url=\"#{request.contextPath}/admin/tracking/track.xhtml\" />\n    34→            <p:menuitem value=\"Live\"\n    35→              url=\"#{request.contextPath}/admin/tracking/map.xhtml\" />\n    36→            <p:menuitem value=\"About\"\n    37→              url=\"#{request.contextPath}/admin/about.xhtml\" />\n    38→          </p:menu>\n    39→        </h:form>\n    40→      </div>\n    41→    </div>\n    42→\n    43→    <!-- Main Section -->\n    44→    <div class=\"ui-g-12 ui-md-10 ui-g-nopad\">\n    45→      <div class=\"ui-g-12 ui-g-nopad\">\n    46→        <div class=\"ui-g\">\n    47→          <ui:insert name=\"content\">Default Content</ui:insert>\n    48→        </div>\n    49→      </div>\n    50→    </div>\n    51→  </div>\n    52→</h:body>\n    53→</html>\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"362c0b15-eddc-43f1-90ca-177813c083a3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013TcSNQQzFgoYrqunwN1in7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<!DOCTYPE html>\n     2→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     3→  xmlns:h=\"http://java.sun.com/jsf/html\" xmlns:f=\"http://java.sun.com/jsf/core\"\n     4→  xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     5→<h:head>\n     6→  <title>Event Logger</title>\n     7→  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" />\n     8→  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n     9→  <h:outputStylesheet name=\"css/app.css\" />\n    10→  <link rel=\"stylesheet\"\n    11→    href=\"//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.3.0/css/font-awesome.min.css\" />\n    12→</h:head>\n    13→<h:body>\n    14→  <h:form>\n    15→    <p:growl id=\"growl\" showDetail=\"true\" life=\"1000\" />\n    16→    <p:wizard flowListener=\"#{eventLogger.onFlowProcess}\"\n    17→      onnext=\"hideBackButton()\" widgetVar=\"eventLogger\">\n    18→\n    19→      <p:tab id=\"trackingIdTab\" title=\"Tracking ID\">\n    20→        <p:panel header=\"Tracking ID\">\n    21→          <p:messages />\n    22→          <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\">\n    23→            <p:selectOneMenu id=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{eventLogger.trackingId}\"\n    24→              required=\"true\" requiredMessage=\"Tracking ID missing\">\n    25→              <f:selectItem itemLabel=\"Tracking ID\" itemValue=\"\"\n    26→                noSelectionOption=\"true\" />\n    27→              <f:selectItems value=\"#{eventLogger.trackingIds}\" />\n    28→            </p:selectOneMenu>\n    29→          </h:panelGrid>\n    30→        </p:panel>\n    31→      </p:tab>\n    32→      <p:tab id=\"locationTab\" title=\"Location\">\n    33→        <p:panel header=\"Location\">\n    34→          <p:messages />\n    35→          <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\">\n    36→            <p:selectOneMenu id=\"locationId\" value=\"#{eventLogger.location}\"\n    37→              required=\"true\" requiredMessage=\"Location missing\">\n    38→              <f:selectItem itemLabel=\"Location\" itemValue=\"\"\n    39→                noSelectionOption=\"true\" />\n    40→              <f:selectItems value=\"#{eventLogger.locations}\" />\n    41→            </p:selectOneMenu>\n    42→          </h:panelGrid>\n    43→        </p:panel>\n    44→      </p:tab>\n    45→      <p:tab id=\"eventTypeTab\" title=\"Event Type\">\n    46→        <p:panel header=\"Event Type\">\n    47→          <p:messages />\n    48→          <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\">\n    49→            <p:selectOneMenu id=\"eventType\" value=\"#{eventLogger.eventType}\"\n    50→              requiredMessage=\"Event type missing\" required=\"true\">\n    51→              <f:selectItem itemLabel=\"Event Type\" itemValue=\"\"\n    52→                noSelectionOption=\"true\" />\n    53→              <f:selectItems value=\"#{eventLogger.eventTypes}\" />\n    54→            </p:selectOneMenu>\n    55→          </h:panelGrid>\n    56→        </p:panel>\n    57→      </p:tab>\n    58→\n    59→      <p:tab id=\"voyageTab\" title=\"Voyage\">\n    60→        <p:panel header=\"Voyage\">\n    61→          <p:messages />\n    62→          <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\">\n    63→            <p:selectOneMenu id=\"voyage\" value=\"#{eventLogger.voyageNumber}\"\n    64→              required=\"false\">\n    65→              <f:selectItem itemLabel=\"Voyage\" itemValue=\"\"\n    66→                noSelectionOption=\"true\" />\n    67→              <f:selectItems value=\"#{eventLogger.voyages}\" />\n    68→            </p:selectOneMenu>\n    69→          </h:panelGrid>\n    70→        </p:panel>\n    71→      </p:tab>\n    72→      <p:tab id=\"dateTab\" title=\"Completion Date\">\n    73→        <p:panel header=\"Completion Date\">\n    74→          <p:messages />\n    75→          <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\">\n    76→            <p:calendar id=\"completionDate\"\n    77→              value=\"#{eventLogger.completionTime}\"\n    78→              pattern=\"#{eventLogger.completionTimePattern}\"\n    79→              requiredMessage=\"A date is needed\" required=\"true\">\n    80→            </p:calendar>\n    81→          </h:panelGrid>\n    82→        </p:panel>\n    83→      </p:tab>\n    84→      <p:tab id=\"confirm\" title=\"Confirmation\">\n    85→        <p:panel header=\"Confirmation\">\n    86→          <h:panelGrid id=\"confirmation\" columns=\"1\" columnClasses=\"grid\">\n    87→            <h:panelGrid columns=\"2\" columnClasses=\"label, value\">\n    88→              <h:outputText value=\"Tracking ID: \" />\n    89→              <h:outputText value=\"#{eventLogger.trackingId}\"\n    90→                styleClass=\"outputLabel\" />\n    91→              <h:outputText value=\"Location: \" />\n    92→              <h:outputText value=\"#{eventLogger.location}\"\n    93→                styleClass=\"outputLabel\" />\n    94→              <h:outputText value=\"Event type: \" />\n    95→              <h:outputText value=\"#{eventLogger.eventType}\"\n    96→                styleClass=\"outputLabel\" />\n    97→              <h:outputText value=\"Voyage number: \" />\n    98→              <h:outputText value=\"#{eventLogger.voyageNumber}\"\n    99→                styleClass=\"outputLabel\" />\n   100→              <h:outputText value=\"Date: \" />\n   101→              <h:outputText value=\"#{eventLogger.completionTimeValue}\"\n   102→                styleClass=\"outputLabel\" />\n   103→            </h:panelGrid>\n   104→          </h:panelGrid>\n   105→          <p:commandButton value=\"Submit\" action=\"#{eventLogger.submit}\"\n   106→            update=\"growl\" process=\"@this\"\n   107→            oncomplete=\"PF('eventLogger').loadStep('trackingIdTab', true)\" />\n   108→        </p:panel>\n   109→      </p:tab>\n   110→    </p:wizard>\n   111→  </h:form>\n   112→  <div class=\"ui-g ui-g-12\">\n   113→    <div class=\"ui-g-offset-5 ui-g-1\">\n   114→      <h:graphicImage value=\"#{resource['/images/CTlogobadge128.png']}\"\n   115→        height=\"68\" alt=\"Cargo Tracker logo badge\" />\n   116→    </div>\n   117→  </div>\n   118→  <script>\n   119→\t\t\tfunction hideBackButton() {\n   120→\t\t\t\t$(\"div.ui-wizard-navbar>button.ui-wizard-nav-back\").css(\n   121→\t\t\t\t\t\t\"display\", \"none\");\n   122→\t\t\t}\n   123→\t\t</script>\n   124→</h:body>\n   125→</html>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"0f3df651-52de-4b90-ba5c-a2edbfb8ccb4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015kUQLQiPDMaUnuPmgeR3xr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\"\n     4→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\">\n     5→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     6→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Cargo Administration</ui:define>\n     7→\n     8→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n     9→    <f:metadata>\n    10→      <f:viewParam name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{itinerarySelection.trackingId}\" />\n    11→      <f:viewAction action=\"#{itinerarySelection.load}\" />\n    12→    </f:metadata>\n    13→\n    14→    <div class=\"ui-g-2\"></div>\n    15→    <div class=\"ui-g-8\">\n    16→      <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{empty itinerarySelection.routeCandidates}\">\n    17→        <p>No routes found that satisfy the route specification. Try setting\n    18→          an arrival deadline further into the future (a few weeks at least).</p>\n    19→      </h:panelGroup>\n    20→    </div>\n    21→  </ui:define>\n    22→</ui:composition>\n    23→</html>\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"08375676-9665-452b-8276-b5db143d7815"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016T7M3MVY7kkPQwW5eP7tyV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n     3→        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n     4→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     5→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     6→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\"\n     7→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     8→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     9→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Cargo Dashboard</ui:define>\n    10→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n    11→    <div class=\"ui-g-2\"></div>\n    12→    <div class=\"ui-g-8\" id=\"container\" style=\"display: none\">\n    13→      <h:form id=\"mainDash\">\n    14→        <ui:include src=\"/admin/tables/list_routed.xhtml\" class=\"clearCargoBkg\" />\n    15→        <br />\n    16→        <br />\n    17→        <ui:include src=\"/admin/tables/list_not_routed.xhtml\" />\n    18→        <br />\n    19→        <br />\n    20→        <ui:include src=\"/admin/tables/list_claimed.xhtml\" />\n    21→      </h:form>\n    22→    </div>\n    23→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.min.js\" />\n    24→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.js\" />\n    25→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/progress.js\" />\n    26→  </ui:define>\n    27→</ui:composition>\n    28→</html>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"56728e27-94c9-44b4-be05-4e313134b6ac"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Cyndh96BbkQVhzaLW1oD1j","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\"\n     4→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\"\n     5→  xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     6→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     7→  <f:metadata>\n     8→    <f:viewParam name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{cargoDetails.trackingId}\" />\n     9→    <f:event type=\"preRenderView\" listener=\"#{cargoDetails.load()}\" />\n    10→  </f:metadata>\n    11→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Cargo Details</ui:define>\n    12→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n    13→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-3\" id=\"leftCol\"></div>\n    14→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-6\" id=\"mainCol\">\n    15→      <br />\n    16→      <p:outputLabel\n    17→        value=\"Routing Details for Cargo #{cargoDetails.cargo.trackingId}\"\n    18→        style=\"font-size: 2em; font-weight: bold\" />\n    19→      <p:separator />\n    20→      <h:panelGrid columns=\"2\" styleClass=\"registrationPanelGrid\"\n    21→        cellpadding=\"5\">\n    22→\n    23→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Origin:\" style=\"color:#5392c3;font-weight: bold;\" />\n    24→        <h:panelGroup>\n    25→          <p:outputLabel value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.originName}\" />\n    26→          <p:outputLabel value=\"&#160;&#160;#{cargoDetails.cargo.originCode}\"\n    27→            style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.9em;\" />\n    28→        </h:panelGroup>\n    29→\n    30→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Destination:\"\n    31→          style=\"color: #5392c3;font-weight: bold;\" />\n    32→        <h:panelGroup>\n    33→          <p:outputLabel value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.finalDestinationName}\" />\n    34→          <p:outputLabel\n    35→            value=\"&#160;&#160;#{cargoDetails.cargo.finalDestinationCode}\"\n    36→            style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.9em;\" />\n    37→        </h:panelGroup>\n    38→\n    39→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Arrival deadline:\"\n    40→          style=\"color: #5392c3;font-weight: bold;\" />\n    41→        <h:panelGroup>\n    42→          <p:outputLabel value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.arrivalDeadline}\" />\n    43→        </h:panelGroup>\n    44→      </h:panelGrid>\n    45→      <p:separator />\n    46→      <br />\n    47→      <div class=\"row\">\n    48→        <div class=\"large-12 columns\">\n    49→          <div id=\"container\" class=\"panel\">\n    50→            <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.routed}\">\n    51→              <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.misrouted}\">\n    52→                <h:panelGrid columns=\"3\" style=\"font-size: 1.2em\"\n    53→                  cellpadding=\"5\">\n    54→                  <p:outputLabel value=\"Misrouted cargo!\"\n    55→                    style=\"vertical-align: top;\" />\n    56→                  <h:form>\n    57→                    <p:button value=\"Reroute\"\n    58→                      outcome=\"selectItinerary.xhtml?faces-redirect=true\"\n    59→                      style=\"font-size:.9em;\">\n    60→                      <f:param name=\"trackingId\"\n    61→                        value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.trackingId}\" />\n    62→                    </p:button>\n    63→                  </h:form>\n    64→                  <p:outputLabel />\n    65→                </h:panelGrid>\n    66→              </h:panelGroup>\n    67→              <p:outputLabel value=\"Itinerary\"\n    68→                style=\"font-size: x-large; font-weight: bold;\" />\n    69→              <br />\n    70→              <br />\n    71→              <p:dataTable var=\"legs\" value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.legs}\"\n    72→                style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    73→                <p:column headerText=\"Voyage\" width=\"64\"\n    74→                  style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    75→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.voyageNumber}\" />\n    76→                </p:column>\n    77→\n    78→                <p:column headerText=\"Load\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    79→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.fromName}  \" />\n    80→                  <br />\n    81→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.fromUnLocode}\"\n    82→                    style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.8em;\" />\n    83→                </p:column>\n    84→\n    85→                <p:column headerText=\"Time\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    86→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.loadTime}\" />\n    87→                </p:column>\n    88→\n    89→                <p:column headerText=\"Unload\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    90→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.toName}\" />\n    91→                  <br />\n    92→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.toUnLocode}\"\n    93→                    style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.8em;\" />\n    94→                </p:column>\n    95→\n    96→                <p:column headerText=\"Time\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    97→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.unloadTime}\" />\n    98→                </p:column>\n    99→              </p:dataTable>\n   100→\n   101→            </h:panelGroup>\n   102→            <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{not cargoDetails.cargo.routed}\">\n   103→              <p>\n   104→                <strong>Not routed</strong> -\n   105→                <h:link value=\"route this cargo\"\n   106→                  outcome=\"selectItinerary.xhtml?faces-redirect=true\">\n   107→                  <f:param name=\"trackingId\"\n   108→                    value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.trackingId}\" />\n   109→                </h:link>\n   110→              </p>\n   111→            </h:panelGroup>\n   112→          </div>\n   113→        </div>\n   114→      </div>\n   115→    </div>\n   116→  </ui:define>\n   117→</ui:composition>\n   118→</html>\n   119→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"34f1a4e7-4dde-4bd9-871e-3e115d4557f4"}
