{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UKT6DmUCvEnJ2GCdGaCbAB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<!DOCTYPE html>\n     2→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     3→  xmlns:h=\"http://java.sun.com/jsf/html\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\"\n     4→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\">\n     5→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     6→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Cargo Registration</ui:define>\n     7→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n     8→    <div class=\"ui-g-2\" id=\"leftCol\"></div>\n     9→    <div class=\"ui-g-8\" id=\"mainCol\">\n    10→      <br />\n    11→      <h:form id=\"dateForm\">\n    12→        <p:outputLabel\n    13→          value=\"3. Set the arrival deadline for this new #{booking.originName}-#{booking.destinationName} cargo \" />\n    14→        <hr />\n    15→        <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\" styleClass=\"registrationPanelGrid\"\n    16→          style=\"margin: 0 auto;\">\n    17→          <p:calendar id=\"deadline\" value=\"#{booking.arrivalDeadline}\"\n    18→            mindate=\"#{booking.today}\" mode=\"inline\" pattern=\"yyyy-MM-dd\">\n    19→            <p:ajax event=\"dateSelect\" listener=\"#{booking.deadlineUpdated}\" />\n    20→          </p:calendar>\n    21→        </h:panelGrid>\n    22→        <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\" id=\"durationPanel\"\n    23→          styleClass=\"registrationPanelGrid\" style=\"margin: 0 auto;\">\n    24→          <p:outputLabel value=\"A journey can't start and end the same day!\"\n    25→            rendered=\"#{booking.duration eq 0}\" />\n    26→          <p:outputLabel value=\"Journey duration is one day.\"\n    27→            rendered=\"#{booking.duration eq 1}\" />\n    28→          <p:outputLabel value=\"Journey duration is #{booking.duration} days.\"\n    29→            rendered=\"#{booking.duration gt 1}\" />\n    30→        </h:panelGrid>\n    31→        <hr />\n    32→        <h:panelGrid columns=\"3\" styleClass=\"registrationPanelGrid\"\n    33→          style=\"margin: 0 auto;\">\n    34→          <p:commandButton value=\"Back\" action=\"booking-destination\" />\n    35→          <p:commandButton value=\"Cancel\" action=\"/admin/dashboard\" />\n    36→          <p:commandButton value=\"Book Cargo\" id=\"bookBtn\"\n    37→            action=\"#{booking.register()}\" disabled=\"#{!booking.bookable}\" />\n    38→        </h:panelGrid>\n    39→      </h:form>\n    40→    </div>\n    41→  </ui:define>\n    42→</ui:composition>\n    43→</html>\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"a1838d38-9bf7-4918-b11e-363e3cc333b6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Pai2FzfirmvriYFuAYdisJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\"\n     4→  xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\" xmlns:f=\"http://java.sun.com/jsf/core\">\n     5→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     6→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Track Cargo</ui:define>\n     7→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n     8→\n     9→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-2\" id=\"leftCol\"></div>\n    10→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-8\" id=\"container\" style=\"display: none\">\n    11→      <br />\n    12→      <div class=\"ui-g ui-g-12\">\n    13→        <div class=\"ui-g-6 ui-g-offset-3\">\n    14→          <h:form id=\"trackingForm\">\n    15→            <h:panelGrid columns=\"3\" cellpadding=\"15\">\n    16→              <p>Enter your tracking ID:</p>\n    17→              <p:autoComplete id=\"trackingIdInput\"\n    18→                value=\"#{admin.track.trackingId}\" required=\"true\"\n    19→                forceSelection=\"true\" placeholder=\"XYZ789\"\n    20→                title=\"Valid tracking ID\"\n    21→                completeMethod=\"#{admin.track.getTrackingIds}\" />\n    22→              <h:commandButton value=\"Track!\"\n    23→                action=\"#{admin.track.onTrackById()}\">\n    24→                <f:ajax execute=\"trackingIdInput\" render=\"cargo-status\" />\n    25→              </h:commandButton>\n    26→            </h:panelGrid>\n    27→          </h:form>\n    28→        </div>\n    29→      </div>\n    30→\n    31→      <div class=\"ui-g-12\">\n    32→        <p:separator />\n    33→      </div>\n    34→      <h:panelGroup id=\"cargo-status\">\n    35→        <div class=\"ui-g-12\">\n    36→          <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{not empty admin.track.cargo}\">\n    37→            <div id=\"result\">\n    38→\n    39→              <p>\n    40→                Cargo <strong><h:link value=\"#{admin.track.trackingId}\"\n    41→                    id=\"trackingId\"\n    42→                    outcome=\"/admin/show.xhtml?faces-redirect=true\"\n    43→                    style=\"text-decoration: none;color: black;\">\n    44→                    <f:param name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{admin.track.trackingId}\" />\n    45→                  </h:link></strong> is currently <strong>#{admin.track.cargo.statusText}</strong>\n    46→              </p>\n    47→\n    48→              <p:tooltip id=\"toolTipFade\" for=\"trackingId\"\n    49→                value=\"Click to see itinerary's details.\" />\n    50→\n    51→              <p>\n    52→                Estimated time of arrival in <strong>#{admin.track.cargo.destination}</strong>:\n    53→                #{admin.track.cargo.eta}\n    54→              </p>\n    55→              <ui:fragment\n    56→                rendered=\"#{not empty admin.track.cargo.nextExpectedActivity}\">\n    57→                <p>#{admin.track.cargo.nextExpectedActivity}</p>\n    58→              </ui:fragment>\n    59→\n    60→              <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{admin.track.cargo.misdirected}\">\n    61→                <p>\n    62→                  <i class=\"fa fa-exclamation-triangle\" style=\"color: #9b2332\"></i>\n    63→                  Cargo is misdirected.\n    64→                </p>\n    65→              </h:panelGroup>\n    66→            </div>\n    67→          </h:panelGroup>\n    68→\n    69→          <h:outputLabel\n    70→            value=\"Cargo with tracking ID #{admin.track.trackingId} not found.\"\n    71→            rendered=\"#{empty admin.track.cargo and not empty admin.track.trackingId}\" />\n    72→        </div>\n    73→\n    74→        <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{not empty admin.track.cargo}\">\n    75→          <div class=\"ui-g ui-g-12\">\n    76→            <div class=\"ui-g-3\">\n    77→              <p:outputLabel value=\"Handling History\"\n    78→                style=\"font-size: 2em; font-weight: bold\" />\n    79→            </div>\n    80→\n    81→            <div class=\"ui-g-12\">\n    82→              <p:separator />\n    83→              <br /> <br />\n    84→            </div>\n    85→\n    86→            <div class=\"ui-g-12\">\n    87→              <ui:repeat value=\"#{admin.track.cargo.events}\" var=\"event\">\n    88→                <div>\n    89→                  <ui:fragment rendered=\"#{event.expected}\">\n    90→                                &#160;&#160;<i class=\"fa fa-check\"\n    91→                      style=\"color: green\" />&#160;#{event.description}, at #{event.time}\n    92→                            </ui:fragment>\n    93→                  <ui:fragment rendered=\"#{!event.expected}\">\n    94→                                &#160;&#160;<em class=\"fa fa-flag\"\n    95→                      style=\"color: #9b2332\" />&#160;#{event.description}, at #{event.time}\n    96→                            </ui:fragment>\n    97→                </div>\n    98→              </ui:repeat>\n    99→\n   100→              <h:outputLabel\n   101→                value=\"There are no events recorded for the tracking ID #{admin.track.cargo.trackingId}.\"\n   102→                rendered=\"#{empty admin.track.cargo.events}\" />\n   103→            </div>\n   104→          </div>\n   105→        </h:panelGroup>\n   106→      </h:panelGroup>\n   107→    </div>\n   108→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.min.js\" />\n   109→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.js\" />\n   110→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/progress.js\" />\n   111→  </ui:define>\n   112→</ui:composition>\n   113→</html>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"8257c341-3e83-4659-88e1-d6c25e0ae0dc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DCgQ6XF5mxzVCUDaLuQC7T","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\">\n     3→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     4→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Live Map</ui:define>\n     5→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n     6→    <div id=\"map\" class=\"ui-g-10 ui-g-offset-1\">\n     7→      <iframe class=\"mapFrame\" width=\"100%\" height=\"960\"\n     8→        src=\"#{request.contextPath}/admin/tracking/mapFrame.xhtml\" />\n     9→    </div>\n    10→  </ui:define>\n    11→</ui:composition>\n    12→</html>\n    13→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"34274d21-de8f-4b3f-8cd4-1156e61d6f36"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HVTVGpZnzUgzBrAf8QoHuf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<!DOCTYPE html>\n     3→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n     4→<head>\n     5→<title>Cargo Live Map</title>\n     6→<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n     7→<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"#{resource['/css/dd.css']}\" />\n     8→<link rel=\"stylesheet\"\n     9→  href=\"//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/twitter-bootstrap/2.3.2/css/bootstrap-combined.min.css\" />\n    10→<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"#{resource['/leaflet/leaflet.css']}\" />\n    11→<script src=\"#{resource['/leaflet/leaflet.js']}\" />\n    12→<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n    13→\t  //  Load the icons for the map.\n    14→\t  const greenIcon = new L.Icon({\n    15→\t      iconUrl: 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pointhi/leaflet-color-markers/master/img/marker-icon-2x-green.png',\n    16→\t      shadowUrl: 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/0.7.7/images/marker-shadow.png',\n    17→\t      iconSize: [25, 41],\n    18→\t      iconAnchor: [12, 41],\n    19→\t      popupAnchor: [1, -34],\n    20→\t      shadowSize: [41, 41]\n    21→\t  });\n    22→\n    23→\t  const greyIcon = new L.Icon({\n    24→\t      iconUrl: 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pointhi/leaflet-color-markers/master/img/marker-icon-2x-grey.png',\n    25→\t      shadowUrl: 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/0.7.7/images/marker-shadow.png',\n    26→\t      iconSize: [25, 41],\n    27→\t      iconAnchor: [12, 41],\n    28→\t      popupAnchor: [1, -34],\n    29→\t      shadowSize: [41, 41]\n    30→\t  });\n    31→\n    32→\t  const redIcon = new L.Icon({\n    33→\t      iconUrl: 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pointhi/leaflet-color-markers/master/img/marker-icon-2x-red.png',\n    34→\t      shadowUrl: 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/0.7.7/images/marker-shadow.png',\n    35→\t      iconSize: [25, 41],\n    36→\t      iconAnchor: [12, 41],\n    37→\t      popupAnchor: [1, -34],\n    38→\t      shadowSize: [41, 41]\n    39→\t  });\n    40→\n    41→\t  const blackIcon = new L.Icon({\n    42→\t      iconUrl: 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pointhi/leaflet-color-markers/master/img/marker-icon-2x-black.png',\n    43→\t      shadowUrl: 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/0.7.7/images/marker-shadow.png',\n    44→\t      iconSize: [25, 41],\n    45→\t      iconAnchor: [12, 41],\n    46→\t      popupAnchor: [1, -34],\n    47→\t      shadowSize: [41, 41]\n    48→\t  });\n    49→\n    50→\t  const goldIcon = new L.Icon({\n    51→\t      iconUrl: 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pointhi/leaflet-color-markers/master/img/marker-icon-2x-gold.png',\n    52→\t      shadowUrl: 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/0.7.7/images/marker-shadow.png',\n    53→\t      iconSize: [25, 41],\n    54→\t      iconAnchor: [12, 41],\n    55→\t      popupAnchor: [1, -34],\n    56→\t      shadowSize: [41, 41]\n    57→\t  });\n    58→\n    59→\t  const colorCodes = {\n    60→\t      \"NOT_ROUTED\": greyIcon,\n    61→\t      \"MISROUTED\": redIcon,\n    62→\t      \"NOT_RECEIVED\": goldIcon,\n    63→\t      \"IN_PORT\": greenIcon,\n    64→\t      \"ONBOARD_CARRIER\": greenIcon,\n    65→\t      \"MISDIRECTED\": redIcon,\n    66→\t      \"AT_DESTINATION\": blackIcon,\n    67→\t      \"CLAIMED\": blackIcon,\n    68→\t      \"UNKNOWN\": redIcon\n    69→\t  };\n    70→</script>\n    71→</head>\n    72→<body style=\"background-color: white\">\n    73→  <div>\n    74→    <div id=\"map\"\n    75→      style=\"height: 600px; border: #FFF; border-style: solid; border-width: 8px;\">\n    76→    </div>\n    77→    <br /> <br />\n    78→    <div id='connected' class='status'>\n    79→      <p id='status' class='status_constent'>offline</p>\n    80→    </div>\n    81→  </div>\n    82→  <script type=\"text/javascript\">\n    83→\t      const statusBox = document.getElementById('connected');\n    84→\t      statusBox.style.cursor = 'pointer';\n    85→\t      statusBox.onclick = function () {\n    86→\t        location.reload(true);\n    87→\t      };\n    88→    </script>\n    89→  <script type=\"text/javascript\">\n    90→\t    var applicationUri = location.protocol + \"//\" + document.location.host;\n    91→\t    const contextRoot = window.location.pathname.split('/')[1];\n    92→\n    93→\t    if (contextRoot == \"cargo-tracker\") {\n    94→\t    \tapplicationUri = applicationUri + \"/cargo-tracker\";\n    95→\t    }\n    96→\n    97→\t    const cargoUri = applicationUri + \"/rest/cargo\";\n    98→\n    99→\t    const windowDimensions = \"height=\" + window.innerHeight + \",width=\" + window.innerWidth;\n   100→\n   101→\t    function specificCargoUri(cargo) {\n   102→\t        return applicationUri + \"/admin/show.xhtml?trackingId=\" + cargo.trackingId;\n   103→\t    }\n   104→\n   105→\t    function coordinates(cargo) {\n   106→\t        return {\n   107→\t            lon: cargo.location.coordinates.longitude +\n   108→\t                    (Math.floor((Math.random() * 4) - 2)),\n   109→\t            lat: cargo.location.coordinates.latitude +\n   110→\t                    (Math.floor((Math.random() * 4) - 2))\n   111→\t        };\n   112→\t    }\n   113→\n   114→\t    function popupContent(cargo) {\n   115→\t        return 'Tracking ID: ' + cargo.trackingId + '&lt;br/>' +\n   116→\t            'Routing status: ' + cargo.routingStatus + '&lt;br/>' +\n   117→\t            'Misdirected: ' + (cargo.misdirected ? \"Yes\" : \"No\") + '&lt;br/>' +\n   118→\t            'Transport status: ' + cargo.transportStatus + '&lt;br/>' +\n   119→\t            'At destination: ' + (cargo.atDestination ? \"Yes\" : \"No\") + '&lt;br/>' +\n   120→\t            'Origin: ' + cargo.origin.name + '&lt;br/>' +\n   121→\t            'Last known location: ' + cargo.lastKnownLocation.name;\n   122→\t    }\n   123→\n   124→\t    function createCargoMarker(cargo) {\n   125→\t        return L.marker(coordinates(cargo), {icon: colorCodes[cargo.statusCode]})\n   126→\t            .bindTooltip(popupContent(cargo))\n   127→\t            .on('click', () => {\n   128→\t                    window.open(specificCargoUri(cargo), \"winMap\", windowDimensions);\n   129→\t            });\n   130→\t    }\n   131→    </script>\n   132→  <script type=\"text/javascript\">\n   133→\t    window.onload = function () {\n   134→\t        const map = L.map('map').setView({lon: 0, lat: 0}, 2);\n   135→\n   136→\t        // Add the OpenStreetMap tiles.\n   137→\t        L.tileLayer('https://{s}.tile.openstreetmap.org/{z}/{x}/{y}.png', {\n   138→\t            maxZoom: 19,\n   139→\t            attribution: '&#xA9;; &lt;a href=\"https://openstreetmap.org/copyright\">OpenStreetMap contributors&lt;/a>'\n   140→\t        }).addTo(map);\n   141→\n   142→\t        // Show the scale bar on the lower left corner.\n   143→\t        L.control.scale().addTo(map);\n   144→\n   145→\t        const cargoMarkers = new Map();\n   146→\n   147→\t        const cargoEventSource = new EventSource(cargoUri);\n   148→\n   149→\t        const status = document.getElementById(\"status\");\n   150→\n   151→\t        cargoEventSource.onopen = function (event) {\n   152→\t            status.innerHTML = \"online\";\n   153→\t        };\n   154→\n   155→\t        cargoEventSource.onmessage = function (event) {\n   156→\t            status.innerHTML = \"updated\";\n   157→\t            const cargo = JSON.parse(event.data);\n   158→\t            const marker = createCargoMarker(cargo);\n   159→\n   160→\t            if (cargoMarkers.has(cargo.trackingId)) {\n   161→\t                cargoMarkers.get(cargo.trackingId).removeFrom(map);\n   162→\t            }\n   163→\n   164→\t            marker.addTo(map);\n   165→\t            cargoMarkers.set(cargo.trackingId, marker);\n   166→\t        };\n   167→\n   168→\t        cargoEventSource.onerror = function (event) {\n   169→\t            status.innerHTML = \"error\";\n   170→\t        };\n   171→\t    };\n   172→    </script>\n   173→</body>\n   174→</html>\n   175→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"7f3050eb-ab31-44c7-96ab-6e4fc54faf14"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01P2zCDH5HpYTsgdQQ8sQceq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     4→<h:head>\n     5→  <title>Change Destination</title>\n     6→</h:head>\n     7→<body>\n     8→  <f:metadata>\n     9→    <f:viewParam name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{changeDestination.trackingId}\" />\n    10→    <f:viewAction action=\"#{changeDestination.load}\" />\n    11→  </f:metadata>\n    12→\n    13→  <div class=\"ui-g full-page\">\n    14→    <h:form>\n    15→      <h:panelGrid columns=\"2\" cellpadding=\"15\">\n    16→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Origin:\" />\n    17→        <p:outputLabel value=\"#{changeDestination.cargo.originName}\" />\n    18→\n    19→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Current destination: \" />\n    20→        <p:outputLabel value=\"#{changeDestination.cargo.finalDestinationName}\" />\n    21→\n    22→        <p:outputLabel value=\"New destination: \" />\n    23→        <p:selectOneMenu value=\"#{changeDestination.destinationUnlocode}\"\n    24→          p:autofocus=\"true\">\n    25→          <f:selectItems value=\"#{changeDestination.potentialDestinations}\"\n    26→            var=\"location\" itemLabel=\"#{location.name}\"\n    27→            itemValue=\"#{location.unLocode}\" />\n    28→        </p:selectOneMenu>\n    29→\n    30→        <p:commandButton value=\"Cancel\"\n    31→          action=\"#{changeDestinationDialog.cancel()}\" />\n    32→\n    33→\n    34→        <p:commandButton value=\"Update\"\n    35→          action=\"#{changeDestination.changeDestination()}\"\n    36→          oncomplete=\"window.location.replace(window.location.href);\" />\n    37→      </h:panelGrid>\n    38→    </h:form>\n    39→  </div>\n    40→</body>\n    41→</html>\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"e2c98235-dbb5-4ad0-9504-b517cddc178c"}
