{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01N5oR8KrwkWR1DENxw4NYbH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     4→<h:head>\n     5→  <title>Change Deadline</title>\n     6→</h:head>\n     7→<body>\n     8→  <f:metadata>\n     9→    <f:viewParam name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{changeArrivalDeadline.trackingId}\" />\n    10→    <f:viewAction action=\"#{changeArrivalDeadline.load}\" />\n    11→  </f:metadata>\n    12→\n    13→  <div class=\"ui-g full-page\">\n    14→    <h:form>\n    15→      <h:panelGrid columns=\"2\" cellpadding=\"15\">\n    16→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Origin:\" />\n    17→        <p:outputLabel value=\"#{changeArrivalDeadline.cargo.originName}\" />\n    18→\n    19→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Destination: \" />\n    20→        <p:outputLabel\n    21→          value=\"#{changeArrivalDeadline.cargo.finalDestinationName}\" />\n    22→\n    23→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Deadline: \" />\n    24→        <p:datePicker value=\"#{changeArrivalDeadline.arrivalDeadline}\" />\n    25→\n    26→        <p:commandButton value=\"Cancel\"\n    27→          action=\"#{changeArrivalDeadlineDialog.cancel()}\" />\n    28→\n    29→        <p:commandButton value=\"Update\"\n    30→          action=\"#{changeArrivalDeadline.changeArrivalDeadline()}\"\n    31→          oncomplete=\"window.location.replace(window.location.href);\" />\n    32→      </h:panelGrid>\n    33→    </h:form>\n    34→  </div>\n    35→</body>\n    36→</html>\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"e46f1d35-e190-4a56-a2a5-64eb29a098b8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GBbCbh7WA9vzBeZna7aAdW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<div id=\"id_list_inprog_cargoes\" xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     2→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     3→  <p:outputLabel value=\"Routed Cargo\" style=\"font-size: 2em; font-weight: bold\" />\n     4→  <p:separator />\n     5→\n     6→  <p:dataTable var=\"cargo\" value=\"#{listCargo.routedUnclaimedCargos}\"\n     7→    style=\"text-align: center;\">\n     8→    <p:column headerText=\"Tracking ID\" width=\"94\">\n     9→      <h:link value=\"#{cargo.trackingId}\" id=\"trackingId\"\n    10→        outcome=\"show.xhtml?faces-redirect=true\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\">\n    11→        <f:param name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{cargo.trackingId}\" />\n    12→        <i class=\"fa fa-info-circle\" style=\"color: #999999;\"></i>\n    13→      </h:link>\n    14→      <p:tooltip id=\"toolTipFade\" for=\"trackingId\"\n    15→        value=\"Click to see itinerary's details.\" />\n    16→    </p:column>\n    17→\n    18→    <p:column headerText=\"Origin\">\n    19→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.originName}  \" />\n    20→      <br />\n    21→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.originCode}\"\n    22→        style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.8em;\" />\n    23→    </p:column>\n    24→\n    25→    <p:column headerText=\"Destination\">\n    26→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.finalDestinationName}\" />\n    27→      <br />\n    28→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.finalDestinationCode}\"\n    29→        style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.8em;\" />\n    30→    </p:column>\n    31→\n    32→    <p:column headerText=\"Last Known Location\">\n    33→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.lastKnownLocationName}\" />\n    34→      <br />\n    35→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.lastKnownLocationCode}\"\n    36→        style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.8em;\"\n    37→        rendered=\"#{!cargo.lastKnownLocationCode.contains('XXXX')}\" />\n    38→    </p:column>\n    39→\n    40→    <p:column headerText=\"Status\">\n    41→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.transportStatus}\" />\n    42→    </p:column>\n    43→\n    44→    <p:column headerText=\"Deadline\">\n    45→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.arrivalDeadline}\" />\n    46→    </p:column>\n    47→\n    48→  </p:dataTable>\n    49→\n    50→  <p:dialog header=\"Tracking Details\" widgetVar=\"ShowTrackingDialog\"\n    51→    modal=\"false\" height=\"200\">\n    52→    <h:outputText value=\"Test --> #{currentTracking.test}\" />\n    53→    <br />\n    54→    <h:outputText value=\"Id --> #{currentTracking.id}\" />\n    55→  </p:dialog>\n    56→</div>\n    57→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"5e0ce9a1-1126-4f51-afad-2846d52eaf9d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TXxpb5hKRR3M7MXvouJw7U","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<div id=\"id_list_compl_cargoes\" xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     2→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     3→  <p:outputLabel value=\"Claimed Cargo\" style=\"font-size: 2em; font-weight: bold\" />\n     4→  <p:separator />\n     5→  <p:dataTable var=\"cargo\" value=\"#{listCargo.claimedCargos}\"\n     6→    style=\"text-align: center;\">\n     7→\n     8→    <p:column headerText=\"Tracking ID\" width=\"94\">\n     9→      <h:link value=\"#{cargo.trackingId}\" id=\"trackingId\"\n    10→        outcome=\"show.xhtml?faces-redirect=true\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\">\n    11→        <f:param name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{cargo.trackingId}\" />\n    12→        <i class=\"fa fa-info-circle\" style=\"color: #999999;\"></i>\n    13→      </h:link>\n    14→      <p:tooltip id=\"toolTipFade\" for=\"trackingId\" value=\"Click to see history.\" />\n    15→    </p:column>\n    16→\n    17→    <p:column headerText=\"Origin\">\n    18→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.originName}  \" />\n    19→      <br />\n    20→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.originCode}\"\n    21→        style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.8em;\" />\n    22→    </p:column>\n    23→\n    24→    <p:column headerText=\"Destination\">\n    25→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.finalDestinationName}  \" />\n    26→      <br />\n    27→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.finalDestinationCode}\"\n    28→        style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.8em;\" />\n    29→    </p:column>\n    30→\n    31→    <p:column headerText=\"Deadline\">\n    32→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargo.arrivalDeadline}\" />\n    33→    </p:column>\n    34→  </p:dataTable>\n    35→</div>\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"1a25f20d-ba44-4d3f-b231-f5767220a744"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BxEwmcX1vACQHSxqeanRPp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<div id=\"id_list_compl_cargoes\" xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     2→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     3→  <p:outputLabel value=\"Not Routed Cargo\"\n     4→    style=\"font-size: 2em; font-weight: bold\" />\n     5→  <p:separator />\n     6→\n     7→  <p:dataTable var=\"cargoNotRouted\" value=\"#{listCargo.notRoutedCargos}\"\n     8→    style=\"text-align: center;\" id=\"tableNotRouted\">\n     9→\n    10→    <p:column headerText=\"Tracking ID\" width=\"94\">\n    11→      <h:link id=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{cargoNotRouted.trackingId}\"\n    12→        outcome=\"/admin/route.xhtml?faces-redirect=true\"\n    13→        style=\"text-decoration: none;\">\n    14→        <f:param name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{cargoNotRouted.trackingId}\" />\n    15→        <i class=\"fa fa-globe\" style=\"color: #999999;\" />\n    16→      </h:link>\n    17→      <p:tooltip id=\"toolTipFade\" for=\"trackingId\"\n    18→        value=\"This cargo is not routed. Click on its tracking ID to route it!\" />\n    19→    </p:column>\n    20→\n    21→    <p:column headerText=\"Origin\">\n    22→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargoNotRouted.originName}  \" />\n    23→      <br />\n    24→      <h:outputText value=\"#{cargoNotRouted.originCode}\"\n    25→        style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.8em;\" />\n    26→    </p:column>\n    27→\n    28→    <p:column headerText=\"Destination\" id=\"ColDest\">\n    29→      <p:commandLink\n    30→        action=\"#{changeDestinationDialog.showDialog(cargoNotRouted.trackingId)}\"\n    31→        style=\"text-decoration: none;\" id=\"toUpdate\">\n    32→        <h:outputText value=\"#{cargoNotRouted.finalDestinationName}  \" />\n    33→        <br />\n    34→        <h:outputText value=\"#{cargoNotRouted.finalDestinationCode}\"\n    35→          style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.8em;\" />\n    36→        <i class=\"fa fa-edit\" style=\"color: #999999;\" />\n    37→        <p:ajax event=\"dialogReturn\"\n    38→          listener=\"#{changeDestinationDialog.handleReturn}\"\n    39→          update=\"tableNotRouted\" />\n    40→        <p:tooltip id=\"updateToolTipFade\" for=\"toUpdate\"\n    41→          value=\"Click to change cargo destination.\" />\n    42→      </p:commandLink>\n    43→    </p:column>\n    44→\n    45→    <p:column headerText=\"Deadline\">\n    46→      <p:commandLink\n    47→        action=\"#{changeArrivalDeadlineDialog.showDialog(cargoNotRouted.trackingId)}\"\n    48→        style=\"text-decoration: none;\" id=\"arrivalDeadlineToUpdate\">\n    49→        <h:outputText value=\"#{cargoNotRouted.arrivalDeadline}  \" />\n    50→        <i class=\"fa fa-edit\" style=\"color: #999999;\" />\n    51→        <p:ajax event=\"dialogReturn\"\n    52→          listener=\"#{changeArrivalDeadlineDialog.handleReturn}\"\n    53→          update=\"tableNotRouted\" />\n    54→        <p:tooltip id=\"updateToolTipFadeArrival\" for=\"arrivalDeadlineToUpdate\"\n    55→          value=\"Click to change cargo arrival deadline.\" />\n    56→      </p:commandLink>\n    57→    </p:column>\n    58→  </p:dataTable>\n    59→</div>\n    60→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"3fdf7ca6-7bf8-42b9-859e-0998557ab2b9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012KoLUcrAyxtzrVmEErzdBh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n     2→<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n     3→        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n     4→<html lang=\"en\" xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\">\n     5→<h:head>\n     6→  <title>Eclipse Cargo Tracker</title>\n     7→  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" />\n     8→  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n     9→\n    10→  <h:outputStylesheet name=\"css/title.css\" />\n    11→\n    12→  <link rel=\"stylesheet\"\n    13→    href=\"//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.3.0/css/font-awesome.min.css\" />\n    14→  <link\n    15→    href=\"http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:300,400,700,300italic,400italic,700italic\"\n    16→    rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\n    17→</h:head>\n    18→<h:body>\n    19→  <div class=\"intro-header\">\n    20→    <div class=\"row\">\n    21→      <div class=\"intro-message\">\n    22→        <hr class=\"intro-divider\" />\n    23→        <a href=\"https://github.com/eclipse-ee4j/cargotracker/\"> <h:graphicImage\n    24→            value=\"#{resource['/images/CTlogobadge128.png']}\"\n    25→            style=\"height: 64px; width: 64px;\" alt=\"Cargo Tracker logo badge\" />\n    26→        </a>\n    27→        <h1 class=\"shadowme animate0\">Eclipse Cargo Tracker</h1>\n    28→        <h2 class=\"shadowme animate0\">Applied Domain-Driven Design\n    29→          Blueprints for Jakarta EE</h2>\n    30→        <div class=\"flex animate1\">\n    31→          <a class=\"button\" href=\"public/track.xhtml\">Public Tracking\n    32→            Interface</a> <a class=\"button\" href=\"admin/dashboard.xhtml\">Administration</a>\n    33→          <a class=\"button\" href=\"javascript:void(0)\"\n    34→            onclick=\"window.open('event-logger/index.xhtml', '_blank', 'width=320,height=440,popup=yes,menubar=no,toolbar=no,location=no,status=no,resizable=yes,scrollbars=yes,titlebar=yes,statusbar=no')\">Event\n    35→            Logging Interface</a>\n    36→        </div>\n    37→        <hr class=\"intro-divider\" />\n    38→      </div>\n    39→    </div>\n    40→  </div>\n    41→</h:body>\n    42→</html>\n    43→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SsvXr6a7XzhL3X8fB5Ba7","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"faf311bc-68d2-4e12-b279-35b3fab78c87"}
