{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014KEt8RRsrnThQZT3fwV7uZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n     2→\n     3→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import javax.faces.annotation.FacesConfig;\n     5→import javax.faces.annotation.FacesConfig.Version;\n     6→\n     7→/** Jakarta Faces configuration. * */\n     8→@FacesConfig(version = Version.JSF_2_3)\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class FacesConfiguration {}\n    11→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"6c919805-22d1-4929-9ba7-bfbc4577a707"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011PvwpDJKfAzCxTJZfqFasK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n     2→\n     3→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location.UNKNOWN;\n     4→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.CHICAGO;\n     5→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.DALLAS;\n     6→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.GOTHENBURG;\n     7→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HAMBURG;\n     8→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HANGZOU;\n     9→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HELSINKI;\n    10→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HONGKONG;\n    11→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.MELBOURNE;\n    12→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.NEWYORK;\n    13→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM;\n    14→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.SHANGHAI;\n    15→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM;\n    16→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.TOKYO;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.Collections;\n    19→import java.util.HashMap;\n    20→import java.util.Map;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    23→\n    24→/**\n    25→ * At the moment, coordinates are produced by a simple factory. It may be converted to a repository\n    26→ * if coordinates become a domain layer concern.\n    27→ */\n    28→public class CoordinatesFactory {\n    29→\n    30→  private static final Map<String, Coordinates> COORDINATES_MAP;\n    31→\n    32→  private CoordinatesFactory() {\n    33→    /* Prevent instantiation. */\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public static Coordinates find(Location location) {\n    37→    return find(location.getUnLocode());\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public static Coordinates find(UnLocode unLocode) {\n    41→    return find(unLocode.getIdString());\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public static Coordinates find(String unLocode) {\n    45→    return COORDINATES_MAP.get(unLocode);\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  static {\n    49→    Map<String, Coordinates> map = new HashMap<>();\n    50→\n    51→    // TODO [Clean Code] See if there is a service to get the latitude/longitude data from.\n    52→    map.put(HONGKONG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(22, 114));\n    53→    map.put(MELBOURNE.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(-38, 145));\n    54→    map.put(STOCKHOLM.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(59, 18));\n    55→    map.put(HELSINKI.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(60, 25));\n    56→    map.put(CHICAGO.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(42, -88));\n    57→    map.put(TOKYO.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(36, 140));\n    58→    map.put(HAMBURG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(54, 10));\n    59→    map.put(SHANGHAI.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(31, 121));\n    60→    map.put(ROTTERDAM.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(52, 5));\n    61→    map.put(GOTHENBURG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(58, 12));\n    62→    map.put(HANGZOU.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(30, 120));\n    63→    map.put(NEWYORK.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(41, -74));\n    64→    map.put(DALLAS.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(33, -97));\n    65→    map.put(UNKNOWN.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(-90, 0)); // The South Pole.\n    66→\n    67→    COORDINATES_MAP = Collections.unmodifiableMap(map);\n    68→  }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"2975b019-92da-4487-897a-b3ef9a35dfbc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XfohqPbrusdLb3PfNdW4M3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * At the moment, coordinates are effectively a shared DTO in the interface layer. It may be\n     5→ * converted to a domain level concern at some point. *\n     6→ */\n     7→public class Coordinates {\n     8→\n     9→  private final double latitude;\n    10→  private final double longitude;\n    11→\n    12→  public Coordinates(double latitude, double longitude) {\n    13→    this.latitude = latitude;\n    14→    this.longitude = longitude;\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  public double getLatitude() {\n    18→    return latitude;\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  public double getLongitude() {\n    22→    return longitude;\n    23→  }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"f1a55d08-3512-4a32-83b8-a6f96ce7ade6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01X7CUpZF6doQ4ueLo4JryUj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.RouteCandidate;\n     9→\n    10→/**\n    11→ * This facade shields the domain layer - model, services, repositories - from concerns about such\n    12→ * things as the user interface and remote communication.\n    13→ */\n    14→public interface BookingServiceFacade {\n    15→\n    16→  String bookNewCargo(String origin, String destination, LocalDate arrivalDeadline);\n    17→\n    18→  CargoRoute loadCargoForRouting(String trackingId);\n    19→\n    20→  CargoStatus loadCargoForTracking(String trackingId);\n    21→\n    22→  void assignCargoToRoute(String trackingId, RouteCandidate route);\n    23→\n    24→  void changeDestination(String trackingId, String destinationUnLocode);\n    25→\n    26→  void changeDeadline(String trackingId, LocalDate arrivalDeadline);\n    27→\n    28→  List<RouteCandidate> requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(String trackingId);\n    29→\n    30→  List<Location> listShippingLocations();\n    31→\n    32→  // TODO [DDD] Is this the right DTO here?\n    33→  List<CargoRoute> listAllCargos();\n    34→\n    35→  List<String> listAllTrackingIds();\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"37b014d3-b42d-4027-88c0-171a4681dcb9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TAzgDjLGQ8uzPyTBY93cKj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     8→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.BookingService;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    23→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n    24→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.RouteCandidate;\n    25→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler.CargoRouteDtoAssembler;\n    26→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler.CargoStatusDtoAssembler;\n    27→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler.ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler;\n    28→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler.LocationDtoAssembler;\n    29→\n    30→@ApplicationScoped\n    31→public class DefaultBookingServiceFacade implements BookingServiceFacade, Serializable {\n    32→\n    33→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    34→\n    35→  @Inject private BookingService bookingService;\n    36→  @Inject private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    37→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    38→  @Inject private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n    39→  @Inject private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    40→  @Inject private CargoRouteDtoAssembler cargoRouteDtoAssembler;\n    41→  @Inject private CargoStatusDtoAssembler cargoStatusDtoAssembler;\n    42→  @Inject private ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler itineraryCandidateDtoAssembler;\n    43→  @Inject private LocationDtoAssembler locationDtoAssembler;\n    44→\n    45→  @Override\n    46→  public List<org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location>\n    47→      listShippingLocations() {\n    48→    List<Location> allLocations = locationRepository.findAll();\n    49→    return locationDtoAssembler.toDtoList(allLocations);\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→  @Override\n    53→  public String bookNewCargo(String origin, String destination, LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    54→    TrackingId trackingId =\n    55→        bookingService.bookNewCargo(\n    56→            new UnLocode(origin), new UnLocode(destination), arrivalDeadline);\n    57→    return trackingId.getIdString();\n    58→  }\n    59→\n    60→  @Override\n    61→  public CargoRoute loadCargoForRouting(String trackingId) {\n    62→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(new TrackingId(trackingId));\n    63→    return cargoRouteDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo);\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  @Override\n    67→  public void assignCargoToRoute(String trackingIdStr, RouteCandidate routeCandidateDTO) {\n    68→    Itinerary itinerary =\n    69→        itineraryCandidateDtoAssembler.fromDTO(\n    70→            routeCandidateDTO, voyageRepository, locationRepository);\n    71→    TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(trackingIdStr);\n    72→\n    73→    bookingService.assignCargoToRoute(itinerary, trackingId);\n    74→  }\n    75→\n    76→  @Override\n    77→  public void changeDestination(String trackingId, String destinationUnLocode) {\n    78→    bookingService.changeDestination(new TrackingId(trackingId), new UnLocode(destinationUnLocode));\n    79→  }\n    80→\n    81→  @Override\n    82→  public void changeDeadline(String trackingId, LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    83→    bookingService.changeDeadline(new TrackingId(trackingId), arrivalDeadline);\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  @Override\n    87→  // TODO [DDD] Is this the correct DTO here?\n    88→  public List<CargoRoute> listAllCargos() {\n    89→    List<Cargo> cargos = cargoRepository.findAll();\n    90→    List<CargoRoute> routes;\n    91→\n    92→    routes = cargos.stream().map(cargoRouteDtoAssembler::toDto).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    93→\n    94→    return routes;\n    95→  }\n    96→\n    97→  @Override\n    98→  public List<String> listAllTrackingIds() {\n    99→    List<String> trackingIds = new ArrayList<>();\n   100→    cargoRepository\n   101→        .findAll()\n   102→        .forEach(cargo -> trackingIds.add(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n   103→\n   104→    return trackingIds;\n   105→  }\n   106→\n   107→  @Override\n   108→  public CargoStatus loadCargoForTracking(String trackingIdValue) {\n   109→    TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(trackingIdValue);\n   110→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n   111→\n   112→    if (cargo == null) {\n   113→      return null;\n   114→    }\n   115→\n   116→    List<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents =\n   117→        handlingEventRepository\n   118→            .lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId)\n   119→            .getDistinctEventsByCompletionTime();\n   120→\n   121→    return cargoStatusDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo, handlingEvents);\n   122→  }\n   123→\n   124→  @Override\n   125→  public List<RouteCandidate> requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(String trackingId) {\n   126→    List<Itinerary> itineraries =\n   127→        bookingService.requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(new TrackingId(trackingId));\n   128→\n   129→    List<RouteCandidate> routeCandidates =\n   130→        itineraries\n   131→            .stream()\n   132→            .map(itineraryCandidateDtoAssembler::toDto)\n   133→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n   134→\n   135→    return routeCandidates;\n   136→  }\n   137→}\n   138→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"8ee33376-21f6-4b21-b6f9-0745ebb7decd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Mzb9juUvngCMPqkDt4Xbfr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto;\n     2→\n     3→public class TrackingEvents {\n     4→\n     5→  private final boolean expected;\n     6→  private final String description;\n     7→  private final String time;\n     8→\n     9→  public TrackingEvents(boolean expected, String description, String time) {\n    10→    this.expected = expected;\n    11→    this.description = description;\n    12→    this.time = time;\n    13→  }\n    14→\n    15→  public boolean isExpected() {\n    16→    return expected;\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  public String getDescription() {\n    20→    return description;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  public String getTime() {\n    24→    return time;\n    25→  }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"ba8235b4-ae51-46ed-88c6-283e9a9e28f9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NAMrvWgXfzekrdMve2nXMX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.Collections;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→\n     7→/** DTO for presenting and selecting an itinerary from a collection of candidates. */\n     8→public class RouteCandidate implements Serializable {\n     9→\n    10→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    11→\n    12→  private List<Leg> legs;\n    13→\n    14→  public RouteCandidate(List<Leg> legs) {\n    15→    this.legs = legs;\n    16→  }\n    17→\n    18→  public List<Leg> getLegs() {\n    19→    return Collections.unmodifiableList(legs);\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→  @Override\n    23→  public String toString() {\n    24→    return \"RouteCandidate{\" + \"legs=\" + legs + '}';\n    25→  }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"ec67485d-d320-424e-b089-41c153526c8a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0192zSeo38bUo4uyRytQ7wgR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import java.util.Collections;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     8→\n     9→/** DTO for registering and routing a cargo. */\n    10→public class CargoRoute implements Serializable {\n    11→\n    12→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    13→\n    14→  private final String trackingId;\n    15→  private final Location origin;\n    16→  private final Location finalDestination;\n    17→  private final String arrivalDeadline;\n    18→  private final boolean misrouted;\n    19→  private final List<Leg> legs;\n    20→  private final boolean claimed;\n    21→  private final Location lastKnownLocation;\n    22→  private final String transportStatus;\n    23→  private String nextLocation;\n    24→\n    25→  public CargoRoute(\n    26→      String trackingId,\n    27→      Location origin,\n    28→      Location finalDestination,\n    29→      LocalDate arrivalDeadline,\n    30→      boolean misrouted,\n    31→      boolean claimed,\n    32→      Location lastKnownLocation,\n    33→      String transportStatus,\n    34→      List<Leg> legs) {\n    35→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    36→    this.origin = origin;\n    37→    this.finalDestination = finalDestination;\n    38→    this.arrivalDeadline = DateConverter.toString(arrivalDeadline);\n    39→    this.misrouted = misrouted;\n    40→    this.claimed = claimed;\n    41→    this.lastKnownLocation = lastKnownLocation;\n    42→    this.transportStatus = transportStatus;\n    43→    this.legs = Collections.unmodifiableList(legs);\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    47→    return trackingId;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public String getOrigin() {\n    51→    return origin.toString();\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  public String getOriginName() {\n    55→    return origin.getName();\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  public String getOriginCode() {\n    59→    return origin.getUnLocode();\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public String getFinalDestination() {\n    63→    return finalDestination.toString();\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  public String getFinalDestinationName() {\n    67→    return finalDestination.getName();\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  public String getFinalDestinationCode() {\n    71→    return finalDestination.getUnLocode();\n    72→  }\n    73→\n    74→  public List<Leg> getLegs() {\n    75→    return legs;\n    76→  }\n    77→\n    78→  public boolean isMisrouted() {\n    79→    return misrouted;\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  public boolean isRouted() {\n    83→    return !legs.isEmpty();\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  public String getArrivalDeadline() {\n    87→    return arrivalDeadline;\n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  public boolean isClaimed() {\n    91→    return claimed;\n    92→  }\n    93→\n    94→  public String getLastKnownLocation() {\n    95→    return lastKnownLocation.toString();\n    96→  }\n    97→\n    98→  public String getLastKnownLocationName() {\n    99→    return lastKnownLocation.getName();\n   100→  }\n   101→\n   102→  public String getLastKnownLocationCode() {\n   103→    return lastKnownLocation.getUnLocode();\n   104→  }\n   105→\n   106→  public String getTransportStatus() {\n   107→    // TODO [Clean Code] This needs to be a richer status, with a more readable description.\n   108→    return this.transportStatus;\n   109→  }\n   110→\n   111→  public String getNextLocation() {\n   112→    return this.nextLocation;\n   113→  }\n   114→}\n   115→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"54bbb585-d0b8-4738-afe4-ad94a17dec51"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QE4NpMjART4HzsxpeLq2ax","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→\n     5→/** Location DTO. */\n     6→public class Location implements Serializable {\n     7→\n     8→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n     9→\n    10→  private String unLocode;\n    11→  private String name;\n    12→\n    13→  public Location(String unLocode, String name) {\n    14→    this.unLocode = unLocode;\n    15→    this.name = name;\n    16→  }\n    17→\n    18→  public String getUnLocode() {\n    19→    return unLocode;\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→  public String getName() {\n    23→    return name;\n    24→  }\n    25→\n    26→  @Override\n    27→  public String toString() {\n    28→    return name + \" (\" + unLocode + \")\";\n    29→  }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"31836ddd-8db0-414a-9209-e80b89167d0f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015JDMEHPtxVb49fHmjTTb9K","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     4→import java.util.Collections;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→\n     7→public class CargoStatus {\n     8→\n     9→  private final String trackingId;\n    10→  private final String destination;\n    11→  private final String statusText;\n    12→  private final boolean misdirected;\n    13→  private final String eta;\n    14→  private final String nextExpectedActivity;\n    15→  private final List<TrackingEvents> events;\n    16→\n    17→  public CargoStatus(\n    18→      String trackigId,\n    19→      String destination,\n    20→      String statusText,\n    21→      boolean misdirected,\n    22→      String eta,\n    23→      String nextExpectedActivity,\n    24→      List<TrackingEvents> handlingEvents) {\n    25→    this.trackingId = trackigId;\n    26→    this.destination = destination;\n    27→    this.statusText = statusText;\n    28→    this.misdirected = misdirected;\n    29→    this.eta = eta;\n    30→    this.nextExpectedActivity = nextExpectedActivity;\n    31→    this.events = new ArrayList<>(handlingEvents.size());\n    32→\n    33→    events.addAll(handlingEvents);\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    37→    return trackingId;\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public String getDestination() {\n    41→    return destination;\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  /** @return A readable string describing the cargo status. */\n    45→  public String getStatusText() {\n    46→    return statusText;\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  public boolean isMisdirected() {\n    50→    return misdirected;\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public String getEta() {\n    54→    return eta;\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  public String getNextExpectedActivity() {\n    58→    return nextExpectedActivity;\n    59→  }\n    60→\n    61→  public List<TrackingEvents> getEvents() {\n    62→    return Collections.unmodifiableList(events);\n    63→  }\n    64→}\n    65→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"588e83cb-c07b-43ec-b495-7256c5a0b733"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QtNJhdRGRcbLEESiLMiSpd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     6→\n     7→/** DTO for a leg in an itinerary. */\n     8→public class Leg implements Serializable {\n     9→\n    10→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    11→  private final String voyageNumber;\n    12→  private final Location from;\n    13→  private final Location to;\n    14→  private final String loadTime;\n    15→  private final String unloadTime;\n    16→\n    17→  public Leg(\n    18→      String voyageNumber,\n    19→      Location from,\n    20→      Location to,\n    21→      LocalDateTime loadTime,\n    22→      LocalDateTime unloadTime) {\n    23→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n    24→    this.from = from;\n    25→    this.to = to;\n    26→    this.loadTime = DateConverter.toString(loadTime);\n    27→    this.unloadTime = DateConverter.toString(unloadTime);\n    28→  }\n    29→\n    30→  public String getVoyageNumber() {\n    31→    return voyageNumber;\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  public String getFrom() {\n    35→    return from.toString();\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  public String getFromUnLocode() {\n    39→    return from.getUnLocode();\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public String getFromName() {\n    43→    return from.getName();\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public String getTo() {\n    47→    return to.toString();\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public String getToName() {\n    51→    return to.getName();\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  public String getToUnLocode() {\n    55→    return to.getUnLocode();\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  public String getLoadTime() {\n    59→    return loadTime;\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public String getUnloadTime() {\n    63→    return unloadTime;\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  @Override\n    67→  public String toString() {\n    68→    return \"Leg{\"\n    69→        + \"voyageNumber=\"\n    70→        + voyageNumber\n    71→        + \", from=\"\n    72→        + from.getUnLocode()\n    73→        + \", to=\"\n    74→        + to.getUnLocode()\n    75→        + \", loadTime=\"\n    76→        + loadTime\n    77→        + \", unloadTime=\"\n    78→        + unloadTime\n    79→        + '}';\n    80→  }\n    81→}\n    82→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"69220c02-b9c3-4d77-84d4-c78ead1911eb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0141ZSmsGkWA4vNCNpH6aP37","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n     4→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.Coordinates;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.CoordinatesFactory;\n     6→\n     7→/** View adapter for displaying a location in a real-time tracking context. */\n     8→public class LocationViewAdapter {\n     9→\n    10→  private final Location location;\n    11→\n    12→  public LocationViewAdapter(Location location) {\n    13→    this.location = location;\n    14→  }\n    15→\n    16→  public String getUnLocode() {\n    17→    return location.getUnLocode().getIdString();\n    18→  }\n    19→\n    20→  public String getName() {\n    21→    return location.getName();\n    22→  }\n    23→\n    24→  public Coordinates getCoordinates() {\n    25→    return CoordinatesFactory.find(location);\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"73c859b2-fc14-4145-a40e-cbc336189ffc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PYJYT8R1H2HygQ7Q1tVh6N","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import javax.annotation.PreDestroy;\n     6→import javax.ejb.Singleton;\n     7→import javax.enterprise.event.ObservesAsync;\n     8→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     9→import javax.ws.rs.GET;\n    10→import javax.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import javax.ws.rs.Produces;\n    12→import javax.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    13→import javax.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→import javax.ws.rs.sse.OutboundSseEvent;\n    15→import javax.ws.rs.sse.Sse;\n    16→import javax.ws.rs.sse.SseBroadcaster;\n    17→import javax.ws.rs.sse.SseEventSink;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi.CargoUpdated;\n    21→\n    22→/** Sever-sent events service for tracking all cargo in real time. */\n    23→@Singleton\n    24→@Path(\"/cargo\")\n    25→public class RealtimeCargoTrackingService {\n    26→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    29→\n    30→  private Sse sse;\n    31→  private SseBroadcaster broadcaster;\n    32→\n    33→  private synchronized void ensureBroadcaster(Sse sse) {\n    34→    if (this.sse == null) {\n    35→      this.sse = sse;\n    36→    }\n    37→    if (broadcaster == null) {\n    38→      broadcaster = this.sse.newBroadcaster();\n    39→      logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE broadcaster created.\");\n    40→    }\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  @GET\n    44→  @Produces(MediaType.SERVER_SENT_EVENTS)\n    45→  public void tracking(@Context SseEventSink eventSink, @Context Sse sse) {\n    46→    ensureBroadcaster(sse);\n    47→\n    48→    cargoRepository.findAll().stream().map(this::cargoToSseEvent).forEach(eventSink::send);\n    49→\n    50→    broadcaster.register(eventSink);\n    51→    logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE event sink registered.\");\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  @PreDestroy\n    55→  public void close() {\n    56→    if (broadcaster != null) {\n    57→      broadcaster.close();\n    58→      logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE broadcaster closed.\");\n    59→    }\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public void onCargoUpdated(@ObservesAsync @CargoUpdated Cargo cargo) {\n    63→    if (broadcaster != null) {\n    64→      logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE event broadcast for cargo: {0}\", cargo);\n    65→      broadcaster.broadcast(cargoToSseEvent(cargo));\n    66→    }\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  private OutboundSseEvent cargoToSseEvent(Cargo cargo) {\n    70→    return sse.newEventBuilder()\n    71→        .mediaType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_TYPE)\n    72→        .data(new RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter(cargo))\n    73→        .build();\n    74→  }\n    75→}\n    76→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"b8fc9759-1d85-4d0a-82e1-b2a2d9ab67d2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LnVBT4JXThZHeZvMqKeRnv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.EnumMap;\n     4→import java.util.Map;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RoutingStatus;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus;\n     8→\n     9→/** View adapter for displaying a cargo in a realtime tracking context. */\n    10→public class RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter {\n    11→\n    12→  private static final Map<RoutingStatus, String> routingStatusLabels =\n    13→      new EnumMap<>(RoutingStatus.class);\n    14→  private static final Map<TransportStatus, String> transportStatusLabels =\n    15→      new EnumMap<>(TransportStatus.class);\n    16→\n    17→  private final Cargo cargo;\n    18→\n    19→  public RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter(Cargo cargo) {\n    20→    this.cargo = cargo;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    24→    return cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString();\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  public String getRoutingStatus() {\n    28→    return routingStatusLabels.get(cargo.getDelivery().getRoutingStatus());\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  public boolean isMisdirected() {\n    32→    return cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected();\n    33→  }\n    34→\n    35→  public String getTransportStatus() {\n    36→    return transportStatusLabels.get(cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus());\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  public boolean isAtDestination() {\n    40→    return cargo.getDelivery().isUnloadedAtDestination();\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  public LocationViewAdapter getOrigin() {\n    44→    return new LocationViewAdapter(cargo.getOrigin());\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  public LocationViewAdapter getLastKnownLocation() {\n    48→    return new LocationViewAdapter(cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation());\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  public LocationViewAdapter getLocation() {\n    52→    return cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus() == TransportStatus.NOT_RECEIVED\n    53→        ? getOrigin()\n    54→        : getLastKnownLocation();\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  public String getStatusCode() {\n    58→    RoutingStatus routingStatus = cargo.getDelivery().getRoutingStatus();\n    59→\n    60→    if (routingStatus == RoutingStatus.NOT_ROUTED || routingStatus == RoutingStatus.MISROUTED) {\n    61→      return routingStatus.toString();\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected()) {\n    65→      return \"MISDIRECTED\";\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isUnloadedAtDestination()) {\n    69→      return \"AT_DESTINATION\";\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    return cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus().toString();\n    73→  }\n    74→\n    75→  static {\n    76→    routingStatusLabels.put(RoutingStatus.NOT_ROUTED, \"Not routed\");\n    77→    routingStatusLabels.put(RoutingStatus.ROUTED, \"Routed\");\n    78→    routingStatusLabels.put(RoutingStatus.MISROUTED, \"Misrouted\");\n    79→\n    80→    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.NOT_RECEIVED, \"Not received\");\n    81→    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.IN_PORT, \"In port\");\n    82→    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.ONBOARD_CARRIER, \"Onboard carrier\");\n    83→    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.CLAIMED, \"Claimed\");\n    84→    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.UNKNOWN, \"Unknown\");\n    85→  }\n    86→}\n    87→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"2e6f3985-304e-48f2-bea7-01681305ba1c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015rLT1U4zeo4xVAseZzNw1M","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import javax.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     6→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     7→import javax.inject.Named;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    11→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Handles changing the cargo destination. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could\n    15→ * easily be rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike\n    16→ * the tracking user interface.\n    17→ *\n    18→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    19→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    20→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    21→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    22→ */\n    23→@Named\n    24→@ViewScoped\n    25→public class ChangeArrivalDeadline implements Serializable {\n    26→\n    27→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    28→\n    29→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    30→\n    31→  private String trackingId;\n    32→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    33→  private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n    34→\n    35→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    36→    return trackingId;\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    40→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    44→    return cargo;\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() {\n    48→    return arrivalDeadline;\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  public void setArrivalDeadline(LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    52→    this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline;\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  public void load() {\n    56→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    57→    arrivalDeadline = DateConverter.toDate(cargo.getArrivalDeadline());\n    58→  }\n    59→\n    60→  public void changeArrivalDeadline() {\n    61→    bookingServiceFacade.changeDeadline(trackingId, arrivalDeadline);\n    62→    PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"DONE\");\n    63→  }\n    64→}\n    65→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"42de821b-9b4c-4394-b73a-77481b4aa6cb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y8jyxFM8zc8JT97o7ELx3Q","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import javax.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     4→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     5→import javax.inject.Named;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * Handles viewing cargo details. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be\n    11→ * rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the\n    12→ * tracking user interface.\n    13→ *\n    14→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    15→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    16→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    17→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    18→ */\n    19→@Named\n    20→@RequestScoped\n    21→public class CargoDetails {\n    22→\n    23→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    24→\n    25→  private String trackingId;\n    26→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    27→\n    28→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    29→    return trackingId;\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    33→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    37→    return cargo;\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public void load() {\n    41→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    42→  }\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"c86b6608-5f46-47c9-ac3a-2948d7173e55"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018qgkqR7tWSUB4anteFR2SU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     9→import javax.faces.application.FacesMessage;\n    10→import javax.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    11→import javax.faces.flow.FlowScoped;\n    12→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    13→import javax.inject.Named;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n    16→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * Handles booking cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be rewritten\n    20→ * as a thick client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the tracking user\n    21→ * interface.\n    22→ *\n    23→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    24→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    25→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    26→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    27→ */\n    28→@Named\n    29→@FlowScoped(\"booking\")\n    30→public class Booking implements Serializable {\n    31→\n    32→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    33→\n    34→  private static final long MIN_JOURNEY_DURATION = 1; // Journey should be 1 day minimum.\n    35→\n    36→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    37→  @Inject private FacesContext context;\n    38→\n    39→  private LocalDate today = null;\n    40→  private List<Location> locations;\n    41→\n    42→  private String originUnlocode;\n    43→  private String originName;\n    44→  private String destinationName;\n    45→  private String destinationUnlocode;\n    46→  private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n    47→\n    48→  private boolean bookable = false;\n    49→  private long duration = -1;\n    50→\n    51→  @PostConstruct\n    52→  public void init() {\n    53→    today = LocalDate.now();\n    54→    locations = bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  public List<Location> getLocations() {\n    58→    List<Location> filteredLocations = new ArrayList<>();\n    59→    String locationToRemove = null;\n    60→\n    61→    if (context.getViewRoot().getViewId().endsWith(\"destination.xhtml\")) {\n    62→      // In the destination menu, origin can't be selected.\n    63→      locationToRemove = originUnlocode;\n    64→    } else { // Vice-versa.\n    65→      if (destinationUnlocode != null) {\n    66→        locationToRemove = destinationUnlocode;\n    67→      }\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    for (Location location : locations) {\n    71→      if (!location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(locationToRemove)) {\n    72→        filteredLocations.add(location);\n    73→      }\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    return filteredLocations;\n    77→  }\n    78→\n    79→  public String getOriginUnlocode() {\n    80→    return originUnlocode;\n    81→  }\n    82→\n    83→  public void setOriginUnlocode(String originUnlocode) {\n    84→    this.originUnlocode = originUnlocode;\n    85→    this.originName =\n    86→        locations\n    87→            .stream()\n    88→            .filter(location -> location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(originUnlocode))\n    89→            .findAny()\n    90→            .get()\n    91→            .getName();\n    92→  }\n    93→\n    94→  public String getOriginName() {\n    95→    return originName;\n    96→  }\n    97→\n    98→  public String getDestinationUnlocode() {\n    99→    return destinationUnlocode;\n   100→  }\n   101→\n   102→  public void setDestinationUnlocode(String destinationUnlocode) {\n   103→    this.destinationUnlocode = destinationUnlocode;\n   104→    this.destinationName =\n   105→        locations\n   106→            .stream()\n   107→            .filter(location -> location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(destinationUnlocode))\n   108→            .findAny()\n   109→            .get()\n   110→            .getName();\n   111→  }\n   112→\n   113→  public String getDestinationName() {\n   114→    return destinationName;\n   115→  }\n   116→\n   117→  public LocalDate getToday() {\n   118→    return today;\n   119→  }\n   120→\n   121→  public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() {\n   122→    return arrivalDeadline;\n   123→  }\n   124→\n   125→  public void setArrivalDeadline(LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n   126→    this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline;\n   127→  }\n   128→\n   129→  public long getDuration() {\n   130→    return duration;\n   131→  }\n   132→\n   133→  public boolean isBookable() {\n   134→    return bookable;\n   135→  }\n   136→\n   137→  public void deadlineUpdated() {\n   138→    duration = ChronoUnit.DAYS.between(today, arrivalDeadline);\n   139→\n   140→    if (duration >= MIN_JOURNEY_DURATION) {\n   141→      bookable = true;\n   142→    } else {\n   143→      bookable = false;\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    PrimeFaces.current().ajax().update(\"dateForm:durationPanel\");\n   147→    PrimeFaces.current().ajax().update(\"dateForm:bookBtn\");\n   148→  }\n   149→\n   150→  public String register() {\n   151→    if (!originUnlocode.equals(destinationUnlocode)) {\n   152→      bookingServiceFacade.bookNewCargo(originUnlocode, destinationUnlocode, arrivalDeadline);\n   153→    } else {\n   154→      // UI now prevents from selecting same origin/destination\n   155→      FacesMessage message = new FacesMessage(\"Origin and destination cannot be the same.\");\n   156→      message.setSeverity(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR);\n   157→      context.addMessage(null, message);\n   158→      return null;\n   159→    }\n   160→\n   161→    return \"/admin/dashboard.xhtml\";\n   162→  }\n   163→\n   164→  public String getReturnValue() {\n   165→    return \"/admin/dashboard.xhtml\";\n   166→  }\n   167→}\n   168→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"94034258-dfec-4818-811b-a249cbee8f71"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XvqEjDG7e6iMr8jTdUot1k","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler;\n     2→\n     3→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.TrackingEvents;\n     9→\n    10→@ApplicationScoped\n    11→public class TrackingEventsDtoAssembler {\n    12→\n    13→  public TrackingEvents toDto(Cargo cargo, HandlingEvent handlingEvent) {\n    14→    String location = locationFrom(handlingEvent);\n    15→    HandlingEvent.Type type = handlingEvent.getType();\n    16→    String voyageNumber = voyageNumberFrom(handlingEvent);\n    17→    return new TrackingEvents(\n    18→        cargo.getItinerary().isExpected(handlingEvent),\n    19→        descriptionFrom(type, location, voyageNumber),\n    20→        timeFrom(handlingEvent));\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  private String timeFrom(HandlingEvent event) {\n    24→    return DateConverter.toString(event.getCompletionTime());\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  private String descriptionFrom(HandlingEvent.Type type, String location, String voyageNumber) {\n    28→    switch (type) {\n    29→      case LOAD:\n    30→        return \"Loaded onto voyage \" + voyageNumber + \" in \" + location;\n    31→      case UNLOAD:\n    32→        return \"Unloaded off voyage \" + voyageNumber + \" in \" + location;\n    33→      case RECEIVE:\n    34→        return \"Received in \" + location;\n    35→      case CLAIM:\n    36→        return \"Claimed in \" + location;\n    37→      case CUSTOMS:\n    38→        return \"Cleared customs in \" + location;\n    39→      default:\n    40→        return \"[Unknown]\";\n    41→    }\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  private String voyageNumberFrom(HandlingEvent handlingEvent) {\n    45→    Voyage voyage = handlingEvent.getVoyage();\n    46→    return voyage.getVoyageNumber().getIdString();\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  private String locationFrom(HandlingEvent handlingEvent) {\n    50→    return handlingEvent.getLocation().getName();\n    51→  }\n    52→}\n    53→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"abbe7aa0-0d15-47da-97f9-aef56221a095"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Sthec9T6yLL1quwJ5Stsgf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Comparator;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     6→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n     8→\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class LocationDtoAssembler {\n    11→\n    12→  public org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location toDto(Location location) {\n    13→    return new org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location(\n    14→        location.getUnLocode().getIdString(), location.getName());\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  public List<org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location> toDtoList(\n    18→      List<Location> allLocations) {\n    19→    List<org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location> dtoList =\n    20→        allLocations\n    21→            .stream()\n    22→            .map(this::toDto)\n    23→            .sorted(\n    24→                Comparator.comparing(\n    25→                    org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location::getUnLocode))\n    26→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    27→    return dtoList;\n    28→  }\n    29→}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"ab18293b-1e61-4c5f-941f-11b5eddb3098"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01V4ZZ81VUDeFv4nUf68G64i","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.util.stream.Collectors.toList;\n     4→\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RoutingStatus;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Leg;\n    13→\n    14→@ApplicationScoped\n    15→public class CargoRouteDtoAssembler {\n    16→\n    17→  @Inject private LocationDtoAssembler locationDtoAssembler;\n    18→\n    19→  public CargoRoute toDto(Cargo cargo) {\n    20→    List<Leg> legs =\n    21→        cargo\n    22→            .getItinerary()\n    23→            .getLegs()\n    24→            .stream()\n    25→            .map(\n    26→                leg ->\n    27→                    new Leg(\n    28→                        leg.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber().getIdString(),\n    29→                        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(leg.getLoadLocation()),\n    30→                        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(leg.getUnloadLocation()),\n    31→                        leg.getLoadTime(),\n    32→                        leg.getUnloadTime()))\n    33→            .collect(toList());\n    34→\n    35→    return new CargoRoute(\n    36→        cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString(),\n    37→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo.getOrigin()),\n    38→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination()),\n    39→        cargo.getRouteSpecification().getArrivalDeadline(),\n    40→        cargo.getDelivery().getRoutingStatus().sameValueAs(RoutingStatus.MISROUTED),\n    41→        cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus().sameValueAs(TransportStatus.CLAIMED),\n    42→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation()),\n    43→        cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus().name(),\n    44→        legs);\n    45→  }\n    46→}\n    47→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"72c0b789-f49f-4499-9637-be7cae586ad4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MgBNFzpN18sTcfp5Yhh3hP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     6→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.RouteCandidate;\n    18→\n    19→@ApplicationScoped\n    20→public class ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler {\n    21→\n    22→  @Inject private LocationDtoAssembler locationDtoAssembler;\n    23→\n    24→  public RouteCandidate toDto(Itinerary itinerary) {\n    25→    List<org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Leg> legDTOs =\n    26→        itinerary.getLegs().stream().map(this::toLegDTO).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    27→    return new RouteCandidate(legDTOs);\n    28→  }\n    29→\n    30→  protected org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Leg toLegDTO(Leg leg) {\n    31→    VoyageNumber voyageNumber = leg.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber();\n    32→    return new org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Leg(\n    33→        voyageNumber.getIdString(),\n    34→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(leg.getLoadLocation()),\n    35→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(leg.getUnloadLocation()),\n    36→        leg.getLoadTime(),\n    37→        leg.getUnloadTime());\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public Itinerary fromDTO(\n    41→      RouteCandidate routeCandidateDTO,\n    42→      VoyageRepository voyageRepository,\n    43→      LocationRepository locationRepository) {\n    44→    List<Leg> legs = new ArrayList<>(routeCandidateDTO.getLegs().size());\n    45→\n    46→    for (org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Leg legDTO :\n    47→        routeCandidateDTO.getLegs()) {\n    48→      VoyageNumber voyageNumber = new VoyageNumber(legDTO.getVoyageNumber());\n    49→      Voyage voyage = voyageRepository.find(voyageNumber);\n    50→      Location from = locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(legDTO.getFromUnLocode()));\n    51→      Location to = locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(legDTO.getToUnLocode()));\n    52→\n    53→      legs.add(\n    54→          new Leg(\n    55→              voyage,\n    56→              from,\n    57→              to,\n    58→              DateConverter.toDateTime(legDTO.getLoadTime()),\n    59→              DateConverter.toDateTime(legDTO.getUnloadTime())));\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    return new Itinerary(legs);\n    63→  }\n    64→}\n    65→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"a6df3c45-cc8e-4876-b939-e057d1dcf083"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01W3xrfxPLe5L3R8y3f3MsrU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     6→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Delivery;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.HandlingActivity;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.TrackingEvents;\n    15→\n    16→@ApplicationScoped\n    17→public class CargoStatusDtoAssembler {\n    18→\n    19→  @Inject private TrackingEventsDtoAssembler assembler;\n    20→\n    21→  public CargoStatus toDto(Cargo cargo, List<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents) {\n    22→    List<TrackingEvents> trackingEvents;\n    23→\n    24→    trackingEvents =\n    25→        handlingEvents\n    26→            .stream()\n    27→            .map(handlingEvent -> assembler.toDto(cargo, handlingEvent))\n    28→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    29→\n    30→    return new CargoStatus(\n    31→        cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString(),\n    32→        cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination().getName(),\n    33→        getCargoStatusText(cargo),\n    34→        cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected(),\n    35→        getEta(cargo),\n    36→        getNextExpectedActivity(cargo),\n    37→        trackingEvents);\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  private String getCargoStatusText(Cargo cargo) {\n    41→    Delivery delivery = cargo.getDelivery();\n    42→\n    43→    switch (delivery.getTransportStatus()) {\n    44→      case IN_PORT:\n    45→        return \"In port \" + delivery.getLastKnownLocation().getName();\n    46→      case ONBOARD_CARRIER:\n    47→        return \"Onboard voyage \" + delivery.getCurrentVoyage().getVoyageNumber().getIdString();\n    48→      case CLAIMED:\n    49→        return \"Claimed\";\n    50→      case NOT_RECEIVED:\n    51→        return \"Not received\";\n    52→      case UNKNOWN:\n    53→        return \"Unknown\";\n    54→      default:\n    55→        return \"[Unknown status]\"; // Should never happen.\n    56→    }\n    57→  }\n    58→\n    59→  private String getEta(Cargo cargo) {\n    60→    LocalDateTime eta = cargo.getDelivery().getEstimatedTimeOfArrival();\n    61→\n    62→    if (eta == null) {\n    63→      return \"?\";\n    64→    } else {\n    65→      return DateConverter.toString(eta);\n    66→    }\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  private String getNextExpectedActivity(Cargo cargo) {\n    70→    HandlingActivity activity = cargo.getDelivery().getNextExpectedActivity();\n    71→\n    72→    if ((activity == null) || (activity.isEmpty())) {\n    73→      return \"\";\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    String text = \"Next expected activity is to \";\n    77→    HandlingEvent.Type type = activity.getType();\n    78→\n    79→    if (type.sameValueAs(HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD)) {\n    80→      return text\n    81→          + type.name().toLowerCase()\n    82→          + \" cargo onto voyage \"\n    83→          + activity.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber()\n    84→          + \" in \"\n    85→          + activity.getLocation().getName();\n    86→    } else if (type.sameValueAs(HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD)) {\n    87→      return text\n    88→          + type.name().toLowerCase()\n    89→          + \" cargo off of \"\n    90→          + activity.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber()\n    91→          + \" in \"\n    92→          + activity.getLocation().getName();\n    93→    } else {\n    94→      return text + type.name().toLowerCase() + \" cargo in \" + activity.getLocation().getName();\n    95→    }\n    96→  }\n    97→}\n    98→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"f253ead7-627e-4a2d-a9ef-70657a2de3cd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Ap9HyEGuFKAGpowZnGqFTp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n     9→\n    10→/**\n    11→ * This is a simple transfer object for passing incoming handling event registration attempts to the\n    12→ * proper registration procedure.\n    13→ *\n    14→ * <p>It is used as a message queue element.\n    15→ */\n    16→public class HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt implements Serializable {\n    17→\n    18→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    19→\n    20→  private final LocalDateTime registrationTime;\n    21→  private final LocalDateTime completionTime;\n    22→  private final TrackingId trackingId;\n    23→  private final VoyageNumber voyageNumber;\n    24→  private final HandlingEvent.Type type;\n    25→  private final UnLocode unLocode;\n    26→\n    27→  public HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n    28→      LocalDateTime registrationDate,\n    29→      LocalDateTime completionDate,\n    30→      TrackingId trackingId,\n    31→      VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n    32→      HandlingEvent.Type type,\n    33→      UnLocode unLocode) {\n    34→    this.registrationTime = registrationDate;\n    35→    this.completionTime = completionDate;\n    36→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    37→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n    38→    this.type = type;\n    39→    this.unLocode = unLocode;\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public TrackingId getTrackingId() {\n    43→    return trackingId;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public VoyageNumber getVoyageNumber() {\n    47→    return voyageNumber;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public HandlingEvent.Type getType() {\n    51→    return type;\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  public UnLocode getUnLocode() {\n    55→    return unLocode;\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  public LocalDateTime getRegistrationTime() {\n    59→    return registrationTime;\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public LocalDateTime getCompletionTime() {\n    63→    return completionTime;\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  @Override\n    67→  public String toString() {\n    68→    return \"HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt{\"\n    69→        + \"registrationTime=\"\n    70→        + registrationTime\n    71→        + \", completionTime=\"\n    72→        + completionTime\n    73→        + \", trackingId=\"\n    74→        + trackingId\n    75→        + \", voyageNumber=\"\n    76→        + voyageNumber\n    77→        + \", type=\"\n    78→        + type\n    79→        + \", unLocode=\"\n    80→        + unLocode\n    81→        + '}';\n    82→  }\n    83→}\n    84→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"f8ca6d27-d058-4757-bfba-335cb692d487"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UNUpSwtma8y8eHmPQ47Ugx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.mobile;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.util.stream.Collectors.toMap;\n     4→\n     5→import java.io.Serializable;\n     6→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     7→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     8→import java.util.Arrays;\n     9→import java.util.Collections;\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→import java.util.Map;\n    12→import java.util.function.Function;\n    13→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    14→import javax.faces.application.FacesMessage;\n    15→import javax.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    16→import javax.faces.model.SelectItem;\n    17→import javax.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n    18→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    19→import javax.inject.Named;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    23→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    24→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    25→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus;\n    26→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    27→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    28→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    29→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    30→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    31→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    32→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    33→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n    34→import org.primefaces.event.FlowEvent;\n    35→\n    36→@Named\n    37→@ViewScoped\n    38→public class EventLogger implements Serializable {\n    39→\n    40→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    41→\n    42→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    43→  @Inject private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    44→  @Inject private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n    45→  @Inject private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    46→  @Inject private FacesContext context;\n    47→\n    48→  private List<SelectItem> trackingIds;\n    49→  private List<SelectItem> locations;\n    50→  private List<SelectItem> voyages;\n    51→\n    52→  private String trackingId;\n    53→  private String location;\n    54→  private HandlingEvent.Type eventType;\n    55→  private String voyageNumber;\n    56→  private LocalDateTime completionTime;\n    57→\n    58→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    59→    return trackingId;\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    63→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  public List<SelectItem> getTrackingIds() {\n    67→    return trackingIds;\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  public String getLocation() {\n    71→    return location;\n    72→  }\n    73→\n    74→  public void setLocation(String location) {\n    75→    this.location = location;\n    76→  }\n    77→\n    78→  public List<SelectItem> getLocations() {\n    79→    return locations;\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  // Move this to a separate utility if it is used in other parts of the UI.\n    83→  public Map<HandlingEvent.Type, HandlingEvent.Type> getEventTypes() {\n    84→    return Collections.unmodifiableMap(\n    85→        Arrays.asList(HandlingEvent.Type.values())\n    86→            .stream()\n    87→            .collect(toMap(Function.identity(), Function.identity())));\n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  public HandlingEvent.Type getEventType() {\n    91→    return eventType;\n    92→  }\n    93→\n    94→  public void setEventType(HandlingEvent.Type eventType) {\n    95→    this.eventType = eventType;\n    96→  }\n    97→\n    98→  public String getVoyageNumber() {\n    99→    return voyageNumber;\n   100→  }\n   101→\n   102→  public void setVoyageNumber(String voyageNumber) {\n   103→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n   104→  }\n   105→\n   106→  public List<SelectItem> getVoyages() {\n   107→    return voyages;\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  public LocalDateTime getCompletionTime() {\n   111→    return completionTime;\n   112→  }\n   113→\n   114→  public void setCompletionTime(LocalDateTime completionTime) {\n   115→    this.completionTime = completionTime;\n   116→  }\n   117→\n   118→  public String getCompletionTimeValue() {\n   119→    return DateConverter.toString(completionTime);\n   120→  }\n   121→\n   122→  public String getCompletionTimePattern() {\n   123→    return DateConverter.DATE_TIME_FORMAT;\n   124→  }\n   125→\n   126→  @PostConstruct\n   127→  public void init() {\n   128→    List<Cargo> cargos = cargoRepository.findAll();\n   129→\n   130→    trackingIds = new ArrayList<>(cargos.size());\n   131→\n   132→    // List only routed cargo that is not claimed yet.\n   133→    cargos\n   134→        .stream()\n   135→        .filter(\n   136→            cargo ->\n   137→                !cargo.getItinerary().getLegs().isEmpty()\n   138→                    && !(cargo\n   139→                        .getDelivery()\n   140→                        .getTransportStatus()\n   141→                        .sameValueAs(TransportStatus.CLAIMED)))\n   142→        .map(cargo -> cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString())\n   143→        .forEachOrdered(trackingId -> trackingIds.add(new SelectItem(trackingId, trackingId)));\n   144→\n   145→    List<Location> locations = locationRepository.findAll();\n   146→\n   147→    this.locations = new ArrayList<>(locations.size());\n   148→\n   149→    locations.forEach(\n   150→        location -> {\n   151→          String locationCode = location.getUnLocode().getIdString();\n   152→          this.locations.add(\n   153→              new SelectItem(locationCode, location.getName() + \" (\" + locationCode + \")\"));\n   154→        });\n   155→\n   156→    List<Voyage> voyages = voyageRepository.findAll();\n   157→\n   158→    this.voyages = new ArrayList<>(voyages.size());\n   159→\n   160→    voyages.forEach(\n   161→        voyage ->\n   162→            this.voyages.add(\n   163→                new SelectItem(\n   164→                    voyage.getVoyageNumber().getIdString(),\n   165→                    voyage.getVoyageNumber().getIdString())));\n   166→  }\n   167→\n   168→  public String onFlowProcess(FlowEvent event) {\n   169→    if (!validate(event.getOldStep())) {\n   170→      return event.getOldStep();\n   171→    }\n   172→\n   173→    if (\"dateTab\".equals(event.getNewStep())) {\n   174→      completionTime = LocalDateTime.now();\n   175→    }\n   176→\n   177→    return event.getNewStep();\n   178→  }\n   179→\n   180→  private boolean validate(final String step) {\n   181→    if (\"voyageTab\".equals(step) && eventType.requiresVoyage() && voyageNumber == null) {\n   182→      FacesMessage message =\n   183→          new FacesMessage(\n   184→              FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR,\n   185→              \"When a cargo is LOADed or UNLOADed a Voyage should be selected, please fix errors to continue.\",\n   186→              \"\");\n   187→      context.addMessage(null, message);\n   188→      return false;\n   189→    }\n   190→\n   191→    return true;\n   192→  }\n   193→\n   194→  public void submit() {\n   195→    VoyageNumber voyage;\n   196→\n   197→    TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(this.trackingId);\n   198→    UnLocode location = new UnLocode(this.location);\n   199→\n   200→    if (eventType.requiresVoyage()) {\n   201→      voyage = new VoyageNumber(voyageNumber);\n   202→    } else {\n   203→      voyage = null;\n   204→    }\n   205→\n   206→    HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt =\n   207→        new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n   208→            LocalDateTime.now(), completionTime, trackingId, voyage, eventType, location);\n   209→\n   210→    applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n   211→\n   212→    FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null, new FacesMessage(\"Event submitted\", \"\"));\n   213→  }\n   214→}\n   215→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"a7c5fbc0-248f-4d39-a0d7-1671f68009c5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KmTF9wZ2dW7NzbssZ2fZ4J","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import javax.annotation.security.PermitAll;\n     4→import javax.batch.operations.JobOperator;\n     5→import javax.batch.runtime.BatchRuntime;\n     6→import javax.ejb.Schedule;\n     7→import javax.ejb.Stateless;\n     8→import javax.ejb.TransactionManagement;\n     9→import javax.ejb.TransactionManagementType;\n    10→\n    11→/**\n    12→ * Periodically scans a certain directory for files and attempts to parse handling event\n    13→ * registrations from the contents by calling a batch job.\n    14→ *\n    15→ * <p>Files that fail to parse are moved into a separate directory, successful files are deleted.\n    16→ */\n    17→@Stateless\n    18→@PermitAll\n    19→@TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.BEAN) // Batch steps manage their own transactions.\n    20→public class UploadDirectoryScanner {\n    21→\n    22→  @Schedule(minute = \"*/2\", hour = \"*\", persistent = false) // In production, run every fifteen minutes\n    23→  public void processFiles() {\n    24→    JobOperator jobOperator = BatchRuntime.getJobOperator();\n    25→    jobOperator.start(\"EventFilesProcessorJob\", null);\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"78a9b4b2-df79-44ca-bad1-8ac1ea3ad0a4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JTSPKZ6QiBbBvKx7BGycy6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.BufferedWriter;\n     4→import java.io.File;\n     5→import java.io.FileWriter;\n     6→import java.io.PrintWriter;\n     7→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     8→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     9→import javax.batch.api.chunk.listener.SkipReadListener;\n    10→import javax.batch.runtime.context.JobContext;\n    11→import javax.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    12→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    13→import javax.inject.Named;\n    14→\n    15→@Dependent\n    16→@Named(\"LineParseExceptionListener\")\n    17→public class LineParseExceptionListener implements SkipReadListener {\n    18→\n    19→  private static final String FAILED_DIRECTORY = \"failed_directory\";\n    20→\n    21→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    22→\n    23→  @Inject private JobContext jobContext;\n    24→\n    25→  @Override\n    26→  public void onSkipReadItem(Exception e) throws Exception {\n    27→    File failedDirectory = new File(jobContext.getProperties().getProperty(FAILED_DIRECTORY));\n    28→\n    29→    if (!failedDirectory.exists()) {\n    30→      failedDirectory.mkdirs();\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    EventLineParseException parseException = (EventLineParseException) e;\n    34→\n    35→    logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Problem parsing event file line\", parseException);\n    36→\n    37→    try (PrintWriter failed =\n    38→        new PrintWriter(\n    39→            new BufferedWriter(\n    40→                new FileWriter(\n    41→                    new File(\n    42→                        failedDirectory,\n    43→                        \"failed_\"\n    44→                            + jobContext.getJobName()\n    45→                            + \"_\"\n    46→                            + jobContext.getInstanceId()\n    47→                            + \".csv\"),\n    48→                    true)))) {\n    49→      failed.println(parseException.getLine());\n    50→    }\n    51→  }\n    52→}\n    53→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"e3f7f16a-0d79-4472-aeca-e0eed6f3d6b4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KyAPyzgUFWuXF13njyBQzb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.BufferedWriter;\n     4→import java.io.File;\n     5→import java.io.FileWriter;\n     6→import java.io.PrintWriter;\n     7→import java.io.Serializable;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import javax.batch.api.chunk.AbstractItemWriter;\n    10→import javax.batch.runtime.context.JobContext;\n    11→import javax.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    12→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    13→import javax.inject.Named;\n    14→import javax.transaction.Transactional;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n    18→\n    19→@Dependent\n    20→@Named(\"EventItemWriter\")\n    21→public class EventItemWriter extends AbstractItemWriter {\n    22→\n    23→  private static final String ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY = \"archive_directory\";\n    24→\n    25→  @Inject private JobContext jobContext;\n    26→  @Inject private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    27→\n    28→  @Override\n    29→  public void open(Serializable checkpoint) throws Exception {\n    30→    File archiveDirectory = new File(jobContext.getProperties().getProperty(ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY));\n    31→\n    32→    if (!archiveDirectory.exists()) {\n    33→      archiveDirectory.mkdirs();\n    34→    }\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  @Override\n    38→  @Transactional\n    39→  public void writeItems(List<Object> items) throws Exception {\n    40→    try (PrintWriter archive =\n    41→        new PrintWriter(\n    42→            new BufferedWriter(\n    43→                new FileWriter(\n    44→                    jobContext.getProperties().getProperty(ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY)\n    45→                        + \"/archive_\"\n    46→                        + jobContext.getJobName()\n    47→                        + \"_\"\n    48→                        + jobContext.getInstanceId()\n    49→                        + \".csv\",\n    50→                    true)))) {\n    51→\n    52→      items\n    53→          .stream()\n    54→          .map(item -> (HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt) item)\n    55→          .forEach(\n    56→              attempt -> {\n    57→                applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n    58→                archive.println(\n    59→                    DateConverter.toString(attempt.getRegistrationTime())\n    60→                        + \",\"\n    61→                        + DateConverter.toString(attempt.getCompletionTime())\n    62→                        + \",\"\n    63→                        + attempt.getTrackingId()\n    64→                        + \",\"\n    65→                        + attempt.getVoyageNumber()\n    66→                        + \",\"\n    67→                        + attempt.getUnLocode()\n    68→                        + \",\"\n    69→                        + attempt.getType());\n    70→              });\n    71→    }\n    72→  }\n    73→}\n    74→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"4524d99e-58ff-405e-b74e-7a490a1f4ece"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017YEqg7CEG8rpkbHG5M26K8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Date;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     5→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     6→import javax.batch.api.listener.JobListener;\n     7→import javax.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     8→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     9→import javax.inject.Named;\n    10→\n    11→@Dependent\n    12→@Named(\"FileProcessorJobListener\")\n    13→public class FileProcessorJobListener implements JobListener {\n    14→\n    15→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    16→\n    17→  @Override\n    18→  public void beforeJob() throws Exception {\n    19→    logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Handling event file processor batch job starting at {0}\", new Date());\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→  @Override\n    23→  public void afterJob() throws Exception {\n    24→    logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Handling event file processor batch job completed at {0}\", new Date());\n    25→  }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"e9ee6ff8-1e22-4b95-8f0a-b79feaec596e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01W7R3djobgDafcSBtdQPr8j","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→public class EventLineParseException extends RuntimeException {\n     4→\n     5→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n     6→\n     7→  private final String line;\n     8→\n     9→  public EventLineParseException(String message, Throwable cause, String line) {\n    10→    super(message, cause);\n    11→    this.line = line;\n    12→  }\n    13→\n    14→  public EventLineParseException(String message, String line) {\n    15→    super(message);\n    16→    this.line = line;\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  public String getLine() {\n    20→    return line;\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"e3afce33-b9d1-4226-a4e5-58a84289f52b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RS4KwZ81mov2TLFjfwfkkk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.File;\n     4→import java.io.RandomAccessFile;\n     5→import java.io.Serializable;\n     6→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     7→import java.time.format.DateTimeParseException;\n     8→import java.util.Arrays;\n     9→import java.util.logging.Level;\n    10→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    11→import javax.batch.api.chunk.AbstractItemReader;\n    12→import javax.batch.runtime.context.JobContext;\n    13→import javax.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    14→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    15→import javax.inject.Named;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n    22→\n    23→@Dependent\n    24→@Named(\"EventItemReader\")\n    25→public class EventItemReader extends AbstractItemReader {\n    26→\n    27→  private static final String UPLOAD_DIRECTORY = \"upload_directory\";\n    28→\n    29→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    30→\n    31→  @Inject private JobContext jobContext;\n    32→  private EventFilesCheckpoint checkpoint;\n    33→  private RandomAccessFile currentFile;\n    34→\n    35→  @Override\n    36→  public void open(Serializable checkpoint) throws Exception {\n    37→    File uploadDirectory = new File(jobContext.getProperties().getProperty(UPLOAD_DIRECTORY));\n    38→\n    39→    if (checkpoint == null) {\n    40→      this.checkpoint = new EventFilesCheckpoint();\n    41→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Scanning upload directory: {0}\", uploadDirectory);\n    42→\n    43→      if (!uploadDirectory.exists()) {\n    44→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Upload directory does not exist, creating it\");\n    45→        uploadDirectory.mkdirs();\n    46→      } else {\n    47→        this.checkpoint.setFiles(Arrays.asList(uploadDirectory.listFiles()));\n    48→      }\n    49→    } else {\n    50→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Starting from previous checkpoint\");\n    51→      this.checkpoint = (EventFilesCheckpoint) checkpoint;\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    File file = this.checkpoint.currentFile();\n    55→\n    56→    if (file == null) {\n    57→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"No files to process\");\n    58→      currentFile = null;\n    59→    } else {\n    60→      currentFile = new RandomAccessFile(file, \"r\");\n    61→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing file: {0}\", file);\n    62→      currentFile.seek(this.checkpoint.getFilePointer());\n    63→    }\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  @Override\n    67→  public Object readItem() throws Exception {\n    68→    if (currentFile != null) {\n    69→      String line = currentFile.readLine();\n    70→\n    71→      if (line != null) {\n    72→        this.checkpoint.setFilePointer(currentFile.getFilePointer());\n    73→        return parseLine(line);\n    74→      } else {\n    75→        logger.log(\n    76→            Level.INFO, \"Finished processing file, deleting: {0}\", this.checkpoint.currentFile());\n    77→        currentFile.close();\n    78→        this.checkpoint.currentFile().delete();\n    79→        File nextFile = this.checkpoint.nextFile();\n    80→\n    81→        if (nextFile == null) {\n    82→          logger.log(Level.INFO, \"No more files to process\");\n    83→          return null;\n    84→        } else {\n    85→          currentFile = new RandomAccessFile(nextFile, \"r\");\n    86→          logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing file: {0}\", nextFile);\n    87→          return readItem();\n    88→        }\n    89→      }\n    90→    } else {\n    91→      return null;\n    92→    }\n    93→  }\n    94→\n    95→  private Object parseLine(String line) throws EventLineParseException {\n    96→    String[] result = line.split(\",\");\n    97→\n    98→    if (result.length != 5) {\n    99→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Wrong number of data elements\", line);\n   100→    }\n   101→\n   102→    LocalDateTime completionTime = null;\n   103→\n   104→    try {\n   105→      completionTime = DateConverter.toDateTime(result[0]);\n   106→    } catch (DateTimeParseException e) {\n   107→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse completion time\", e, line);\n   108→    }\n   109→\n   110→    TrackingId trackingId = null;\n   111→\n   112→    try {\n   113→      trackingId = new TrackingId(result[1]);\n   114→    } catch (NullPointerException e) {\n   115→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse tracking ID\", e, line);\n   116→    }\n   117→\n   118→    VoyageNumber voyageNumber = null;\n   119→\n   120→    try {\n   121→      if (!result[2].isEmpty()) {\n   122→        voyageNumber = new VoyageNumber(result[2]);\n   123→      }\n   124→    } catch (NullPointerException e) {\n   125→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse voyage number\", e, line);\n   126→    }\n   127→\n   128→    UnLocode unLocode = null;\n   129→\n   130→    try {\n   131→      unLocode = new UnLocode(result[3]);\n   132→    } catch (IllegalArgumentException | NullPointerException e) {\n   133→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse UN location code\", e, line);\n   134→    }\n   135→\n   136→    HandlingEvent.Type eventType = null;\n   137→\n   138→    try {\n   139→      eventType = HandlingEvent.Type.valueOf(result[4]);\n   140→    } catch (IllegalArgumentException | NullPointerException e) {\n   141→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse event type\", e, line);\n   142→    }\n   143→\n   144→    HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt =\n   145→        new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n   146→            LocalDateTime.now(), completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, eventType, unLocode);\n   147→\n   148→    return attempt;\n   149→  }\n   150→\n   151→  @Override\n   152→  public Serializable checkpointInfo() throws Exception {\n   153→    return this.checkpoint;\n   154→  }\n   155→}\n   156→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"6f6b2568-9756-4c7e-816d-f3da0993c136"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DutGYXoy9cCwVBcfDcMw5U","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.File;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→import java.util.LinkedList;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→\n     8→public class EventFilesCheckpoint implements Serializable {\n     9→\n    10→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    11→\n    12→  private List<File> files = new LinkedList<>();\n    13→  private int fileIndex = 0;\n    14→  private long filePointer = 0;\n    15→\n    16→  public void setFiles(List<File> files) {\n    17→    this.files = files;\n    18→  }\n    19→\n    20→  public long getFilePointer() {\n    21→    return filePointer;\n    22→  }\n    23→\n    24→  public void setFilePointer(long filePointer) {\n    25→    this.filePointer = filePointer;\n    26→  }\n    27→\n    28→  public File currentFile() {\n    29→    if (files.size() > fileIndex) {\n    30→      return files.get(fileIndex);\n    31→    } else {\n    32→      return null;\n    33→    }\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public File nextFile() {\n    37→    filePointer = 0;\n    38→\n    39→    if (files.size() > ++fileIndex) {\n    40→      return files.get(fileIndex);\n    41→    } else {\n    42→      return null;\n    43→    }\n    44→  }\n    45→}\n    46→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"6acc641d-be2a-494b-b609-bd0cb6c2ddeb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017fbjLr3YaExc8bU9STVx4R","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     6→import javax.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     7→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     8→import javax.inject.Named;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n    11→\n    12→/**\n    13→ * Handles tracking cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be\n    14→ * rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the public\n    15→ * tracking user interface.\n    16→ *\n    17→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    18→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the public tracking controller. However,\n    19→ * there is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    20→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    21→ */\n    22→@Named(\"admin.track\")\n    23→@ViewScoped\n    24→public class Track implements Serializable {\n    25→\n    26→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    29→\n    30→  private List<String> trackingIds;\n    31→  private String trackingId;\n    32→  private CargoStatus cargo;\n    33→\n    34→  public List<String> getTrackingIds(String query) {\n    35→    return trackingIds;\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    39→    return trackingId;\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    43→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public CargoStatus getCargo() {\n    47→    return this.cargo;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  @PostConstruct\n    51→  public void init() {\n    52→    trackingIds = bookingServiceFacade.listAllTrackingIds();\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  public void onTrackById() {\n    56→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(this.trackingId);\n    57→  }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"02185c38-d060-4047-9758-662eeeccc432"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01X5NaVNyyGfqytbhMGY2DPb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.HashMap;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.Map;\n     8→import javax.enterprise.context.SessionScoped;\n     9→import javax.inject.Named;\n    10→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    11→import org.primefaces.event.SelectEvent;\n    12→\n    13→@Named\n    14→@SessionScoped\n    15→public class ChangeDestinationDialog implements Serializable {\n    16→\n    17→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    18→\n    19→  public void showDialog(String trackingId) {\n    20→    Map<String, Object> options = new HashMap<>();\n    21→    options.put(\"modal\", true);\n    22→    options.put(\"draggable\", true);\n    23→    options.put(\"resizable\", false);\n    24→    options.put(\"contentWidth\", 410);\n    25→    options.put(\"contentHeight\", 280);\n    26→\n    27→    Map<String, List<String>> params = new HashMap<>();\n    28→    List<String> values = new ArrayList<>();\n    29→    values.add(trackingId);\n    30→    params.put(\"trackingId\", values);\n    31→\n    32→    PrimeFaces.current()\n    33→        .dialog()\n    34→        .openDynamic(\"/admin/dialogs/change_destination.xhtml\", options, params);\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  public void handleReturn(@SuppressWarnings(\"rawtypes\") SelectEvent event) {}\n    38→\n    39→  public void cancel() {\n    40→    // just kill the dialog\n    41→    PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"\");\n    42→  }\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"d2f81512-fd3b-474b-89cf-87fc35654dac"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Rz7hy7YHTMQeNAxFUoaHQM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.util.stream.Collectors.toList;\n     4→\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     7→import javax.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     8→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     9→import javax.inject.Named;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Handles listing cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be rewritten\n    15→ * as a thick client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the tracking user\n    16→ * interface.\n    17→ *\n    18→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    19→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    20→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    21→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    22→ */\n    23→@Named\n    24→@RequestScoped\n    25→public class ListCargo {\n    26→\n    27→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    28→\n    29→  private List<CargoRoute> notRoutedCargos;\n    30→  private List<CargoRoute> routedUnclaimedCargos;\n    31→  private List<CargoRoute> claimedCargos;\n    32→\n    33→  @PostConstruct\n    34→  public void init() {\n    35→    List<CargoRoute> cargos = bookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos();\n    36→    notRoutedCargos = cargos.stream().filter(route -> !route.isRouted()).collect(toList());\n    37→    routedUnclaimedCargos =\n    38→        cargos.stream().filter(route -> route.isRouted() && !route.isClaimed()).collect(toList());\n    39→    claimedCargos = cargos.stream().filter(CargoRoute::isClaimed).collect(toList());\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public List<CargoRoute> getNotRoutedCargos() {\n    43→    return notRoutedCargos;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public List<CargoRoute> getRoutedUnclaimedCargos() {\n    47→    return routedUnclaimedCargos;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public List<CargoRoute> getClaimedCargos() {\n    51→    return claimedCargos;\n    52→  }\n    53→}\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"792392f3-210c-4701-911a-135cb08dcdbc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011xzxwMSAstkEYWrgTHzqd6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     6→import javax.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     7→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     8→import javax.inject.Named;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n    12→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    13→\n    14→/**\n    15→ * Handles changing the cargo destination. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could\n    16→ * easily be rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike\n    17→ * the tracking user interface.\n    18→ *\n    19→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    20→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    21→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    22→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    23→ */\n    24→@Named\n    25→@ViewScoped\n    26→public class ChangeDestination implements Serializable {\n    27→\n    28→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    29→\n    30→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    31→\n    32→  private String trackingId;\n    33→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    34→  private List<Location> locations;\n    35→  private String destinationUnlocode;\n    36→\n    37→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    38→    return trackingId;\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    42→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    46→    return cargo;\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  public List<Location> getLocations() {\n    50→    return locations;\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public List<Location> getPotentialDestinations() {\n    54→    // Potential destination = All Locations - Origin - Current Destination\n    55→    List<Location> destinationsToRemove =\n    56→        locations\n    57→            .stream()\n    58→            .filter(\n    59→                location ->\n    60→                    location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(cargo.getOriginCode())\n    61→                        || location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(cargo.getFinalDestinationCode()))\n    62→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    63→\n    64→    locations.removeAll(destinationsToRemove);\n    65→\n    66→    return locations;\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  public String getDestinationUnlocode() {\n    70→    return destinationUnlocode;\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  public void setDestinationUnlocode(String destinationUnlocode) {\n    74→    this.destinationUnlocode = destinationUnlocode;\n    75→  }\n    76→\n    77→  public void load() {\n    78→    locations = bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n    79→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  public void changeDestination() {\n    83→    bookingServiceFacade.changeDestination(trackingId, destinationUnlocode);\n    84→    // PF.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"DONE\");\n    85→    PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"DONE\");\n    86→    // RequestContext.getCurrentInstance().closeDialog(\"DONE\");\n    87→  }\n    88→}\n    89→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"c525a154-464d-46ef-ace7-a9acb9123c45"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01N5vgFE1SLGiYmjt3MMsAn4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import javax.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     6→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     7→import javax.inject.Named;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.RouteCandidate;\n    11→\n    12→/**\n    13→ * Handles itinerary selection. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be\n    14→ * rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the\n    15→ * tracking user interface.\n    16→ *\n    17→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    18→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    19→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    20→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    21→ */\n    22→@Named\n    23→@ViewScoped\n    24→public class ItinerarySelection implements Serializable {\n    25→\n    26→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    29→\n    30→  List<RouteCandidate> routeCandidates;\n    31→  private String trackingId;\n    32→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    33→\n    34→  public List<RouteCandidate> getRouteCandidates() {\n    35→    return routeCandidates;\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    39→    return trackingId;\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    43→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    47→    return cargo;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public List<RouteCandidate> getRouteCanditates() {\n    51→    return routeCandidates;\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  public void load() {\n    55→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    56→    routeCandidates = bookingServiceFacade.requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(trackingId);\n    57→  }\n    58→\n    59→  public String assignItinerary(int routeIndex) {\n    60→    RouteCandidate route = routeCandidates.get(routeIndex);\n    61→    bookingServiceFacade.assignCargoToRoute(trackingId, route);\n    62→\n    63→    return \"show.html?faces-redirect=true&trackingId=\" + trackingId;\n    64→  }\n    65→}\n    66→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"e2f6112f-2b44-4c8b-a587-dede84a2baa2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Arg1YmW2s7dvtuycrCQYEu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.HashMap;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.Map;\n     8→import javax.enterprise.context.SessionScoped;\n     9→import javax.inject.Named;\n    10→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    11→import org.primefaces.event.SelectEvent;\n    12→\n    13→@Named\n    14→@SessionScoped\n    15→public class ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog implements Serializable {\n    16→\n    17→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    18→\n    19→  public void showDialog(String trackingId) {\n    20→    Map<String, Object> options = new HashMap<>();\n    21→    options.put(\"modal\", true);\n    22→    options.put(\"draggable\", true);\n    23→    options.put(\"resizable\", false);\n    24→    options.put(\"contentWidth\", 410);\n    25→    options.put(\"contentHeight\", 280);\n    26→\n    27→    Map<String, List<String>> params = new HashMap<>();\n    28→    List<String> values = new ArrayList<>();\n    29→    values.add(trackingId);\n    30→    params.put(\"trackingId\", values);\n    31→\n    32→    PrimeFaces.current()\n    33→        .dialog()\n    34→        .openDynamic(\"/admin/dialogs/change_arrival_deadline.xhtml\", options, params);\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  public void handleReturn(@SuppressWarnings(\"rawtypes\") SelectEvent event) {}\n    38→\n    39→  public void cancel() {\n    40→    // just kill the dialog\n    41→    PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"\");\n    42→  }\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"44d56dc8-0e80-4602-8aac-54f4f5531a34"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016z186ZLPcyJnnMxgRvSztT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.tracking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets.UTF_8;\n     4→\n     5→import java.io.Serializable;\n     6→import java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException;\n     7→import java.net.URLEncoder;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import java.util.logging.Level;\n    10→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    11→import javax.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n    12→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    13→import javax.inject.Named;\n    14→import javax.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    20→\n    21→/**\n    22→ * Backing bean for tracking cargo. This interface sits immediately on top of the domain layer,\n    23→ * unlike the booking interface which has a facade and supporting DTOs in between.\n    24→ *\n    25→ * <p>An adapter class, designed for the tracking use case, is used to wrap the domain model to make\n    26→ * it easier to work with in a web page rendering context. We do not want to apply view rendering\n    27→ * constraints to the design of our domain model and the adapter helps us shield the domain model\n    28→ * classes where needed.\n    29→ *\n    30→ * <p>In some very simplistic cases, it is fine to not use even an adapter.\n    31→ */\n    32→@Named(\"public.track\")\n    33→@ViewScoped\n    34→public class Track implements Serializable {\n    35→\n    36→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    37→\n    38→  @Inject private transient Logger logger;\n    39→\n    40→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    41→  @Inject private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    42→\n    43→  private String trackingId;\n    44→  private CargoTrackingViewAdapter cargo;\n    45→\n    46→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    47→    return trackingId;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    51→    if (trackingId != null) {\n    52→      trackingId = trackingId.trim();\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  public CargoTrackingViewAdapter getCargo() {\n    59→    return cargo;\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public String getCargoAsJson() {\n    63→    try {\n    64→      return URLEncoder.encode(JsonbBuilder.create().toJson(cargo), UTF_8.name());\n    65→    } catch (UnsupportedEncodingException ex) {\n    66→      logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"URL encoding error.\", ex);\n    67→      return \"\"; // Should never happen.\n    68→    }\n    69→  }\n    70→\n    71→  public void onTrackById() {\n    72→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(new TrackingId(trackingId));\n    73→\n    74→    if (cargo != null) {\n    75→      List<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents =\n    76→          handlingEventRepository\n    77→              .lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(new TrackingId(trackingId))\n    78→              .getDistinctEventsByCompletionTime();\n    79→      this.cargo = new CargoTrackingViewAdapter(cargo, handlingEvents);\n    80→    } else {\n    81→      this.cargo = null;\n    82→    }\n    83→  }\n    84→}\n    85→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"72bc734e-682b-40d5-976d-70d7184fc69b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0167ibeZrYa3f8KnKpKygR3p","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.tracking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.Collections;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Delivery;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.HandlingActivity;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.Coordinates;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.CoordinatesFactory;\n    14→\n    15→/** View adapter for displaying a cargo in a tracking context. */\n    16→public class CargoTrackingViewAdapter {\n    17→\n    18→  private final Cargo cargo;\n    19→  private final List<HandlingEventViewAdapter> events;\n    20→\n    21→  public CargoTrackingViewAdapter(Cargo cargo, List<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents) {\n    22→    this.cargo = cargo;\n    23→    this.events = new ArrayList<>(handlingEvents.size());\n    24→\n    25→    handlingEvents.stream().map(HandlingEventViewAdapter::new).forEach(events::add);\n    26→  }\n    27→\n    28→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    29→    return cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString();\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  public String getOriginName() {\n    33→    return cargo.getRouteSpecification().getOrigin().getName();\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public String getOriginCode() {\n    37→    return cargo.getRouteSpecification().getOrigin().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public Coordinates getOriginCoordinates() {\n    41→    return CoordinatesFactory.find(cargo.getRouteSpecification().getOrigin());\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public String getDestinationName() {\n    45→    return cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination().getName();\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  public String getDestinationCode() {\n    49→    return cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→  public Coordinates getDestinationCoordinates() {\n    53→    return CoordinatesFactory.find(cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination());\n    54→  }\n    55→\n    56→  public String getLastKnownLocationName() {\n    57→    return cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation().getUnLocode().getIdString().equals(\"XXXXX\")\n    58→        ? \"Unknown\"\n    59→        : cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation().getName();\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public String getLastKnownLocationCode() {\n    63→    return cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  public Coordinates getLastKnownLocationCoordinates() {\n    67→    return CoordinatesFactory.find(cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation());\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  public String getStatusCode() {\n    71→    if (cargo.getItinerary().getLegs().isEmpty()) {\n    72→      return \"NOT_ROUTED\";\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isUnloadedAtDestination()) {\n    76→      return \"AT_DESTINATION\";\n    77→    }\n    78→\n    79→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected()) {\n    80→      return \"MISDIRECTED\";\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    return cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus().name();\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  /** @return A readable string describing the cargo status. */\n    87→  public String getStatusText() {\n    88→    Delivery delivery = cargo.getDelivery();\n    89→\n    90→    switch (delivery.getTransportStatus()) {\n    91→      case IN_PORT:\n    92→        return \"In port \" + cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination().getName();\n    93→      case ONBOARD_CARRIER:\n    94→        return \"Onboard voyage \" + delivery.getCurrentVoyage().getVoyageNumber().getIdString();\n    95→      case CLAIMED:\n    96→        return \"Claimed\";\n    97→      case NOT_RECEIVED:\n    98→        return \"Not received\";\n    99→      case UNKNOWN:\n   100→        return \"Unknown\";\n   101→      default:\n   102→        return \"[Unknown status]\"; // Should never happen.\n   103→    }\n   104→  }\n   105→\n   106→  public boolean isMisdirected() {\n   107→    return cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected();\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  public String getEta() {\n   111→    LocalDateTime eta = cargo.getDelivery().getEstimatedTimeOfArrival();\n   112→\n   113→    if (eta == null) {\n   114→      return \"?\";\n   115→    } else {\n   116→      return DateConverter.toString(eta);\n   117→    }\n   118→  }\n   119→\n   120→  public String getNextExpectedActivity() {\n   121→    HandlingActivity activity = cargo.getDelivery().getNextExpectedActivity();\n   122→\n   123→    if ((activity == null) || (activity.isEmpty())) {\n   124→      return \"\";\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    String text = \"Next expected activity is to \";\n   128→    HandlingEvent.Type type = activity.getType();\n   129→\n   130→    if (type.sameValueAs(HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD)) {\n   131→      return text\n   132→          + type.name().toLowerCase()\n   133→          + \" cargo onto voyage \"\n   134→          + activity.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber()\n   135→          + \" in \"\n   136→          + activity.getLocation().getName();\n   137→    } else if (type.sameValueAs(HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD)) {\n   138→      return text\n   139→          + type.name().toLowerCase()\n   140→          + \" cargo off of \"\n   141→          + activity.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber()\n   142→          + \" in \"\n   143→          + activity.getLocation().getName();\n   144→    } else {\n   145→      return text + type.name().toLowerCase() + \" cargo in \" + activity.getLocation().getName();\n   146→    }\n   147→  }\n   148→\n   149→  /** @return An unmodifiable list of handling event view adapters. */\n   150→  public List<HandlingEventViewAdapter> getEvents() {\n   151→    return Collections.unmodifiableList(events);\n   152→  }\n   153→\n   154→  /** Handling event view adapter component. */\n   155→  public class HandlingEventViewAdapter {\n   156→\n   157→    private final HandlingEvent handlingEvent;\n   158→\n   159→    public HandlingEventViewAdapter(HandlingEvent handlingEvent) {\n   160→      this.handlingEvent = handlingEvent;\n   161→    }\n   162→\n   163→    public String getTime() {\n   164→      return DateConverter.toString(handlingEvent.getCompletionTime());\n   165→    }\n   166→\n   167→    public boolean isExpected() {\n   168→      return cargo.getItinerary().isExpected(handlingEvent);\n   169→    }\n   170→\n   171→    public String getDescription() {\n   172→      switch (handlingEvent.getType()) {\n   173→        case LOAD:\n   174→          return \"Loaded onto voyage \"\n   175→              + handlingEvent.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber().getIdString()\n   176→              + \" in \"\n   177→              + handlingEvent.getLocation().getName();\n   178→        case UNLOAD:\n   179→          return \"Unloaded off voyage \"\n   180→              + handlingEvent.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber().getIdString()\n   181→              + \" in \"\n   182→              + handlingEvent.getLocation().getName();\n   183→        case RECEIVE:\n   184→          return \"Received in \" + handlingEvent.getLocation().getName();\n   185→        case CLAIM:\n   186→          return \"Claimed in \" + handlingEvent.getLocation().getName();\n   187→        case CUSTOMS:\n   188→          return \"Cleared customs in \" + handlingEvent.getLocation().getName();\n   189→        default:\n   190→          return \"[Unknown]\";\n   191→      }\n   192→    }\n   193→  }\n   194→}\n   195→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"2f7a6976-18c5-4e74-8f3e-9b138787d05d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015x4oAirv6AtMs5cRjgTUNW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.rest;\n     2→\n     3→import javax.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     4→import javax.validation.constraints.Size;\n     5→import javax.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;\n     6→\n     7→/** Transfer object for handling reports. */\n     8→@XmlRootElement\n     9→public class HandlingReport {\n    10→\n    11→  @NotBlank(message = \"Missing completion time.\")\n    12→  @Size(\n    13→      min = 15,\n    14→      max = 19,\n    15→      message = \"Completion time value must be between fifteen and nineteen characters long.\")\n    16→  // TODO [DDD] Apply regular expression validation.\n    17→  private String completionTime;\n    18→\n    19→  @NotBlank(message = \"Missing tracking ID.\")\n    20→  @Size(min = 4, message = \"Tracking ID must be at least four characters.\")\n    21→  private String trackingId;\n    22→\n    23→  @NotBlank(message = \"Missing event type.\")\n    24→  @Size(\n    25→      min = 4,\n    26→      max = 7,\n    27→      message = \"Event type value must be one of: RECEIVE, LOAD, UNLOAD, CUSTOMS, CLAIM\")\n    28→  // TODO [DDD] Apply regular expression validation.\n    29→  private String eventType;\n    30→\n    31→  @NotBlank(message = \"UN location code missing.\")\n    32→  @Size(min = 5, max = 5, message = \"UN location code must be five characters long.\")\n    33→  private String unLocode;\n    34→\n    35→  @Size(\n    36→      min = 4,\n    37→      max = 5,\n    38→      message = \"Voyage number value must be between four and five characters long.\")\n    39→  private String voyageNumber;\n    40→\n    41→  public String getCompletionTime() {\n    42→    return completionTime;\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  public void setCompletionTime(String value) {\n    46→    this.completionTime = value;\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    50→    return trackingId;\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    54→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  public String getEventType() {\n    58→    return eventType;\n    59→  }\n    60→\n    61→  public void setEventType(String value) {\n    62→    this.eventType = value;\n    63→  }\n    64→\n    65→  public String getUnLocode() {\n    66→    return unLocode;\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  public void setUnLocode(String value) {\n    70→    this.unLocode = value;\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  public String getVoyageNumber() {\n    74→    return voyageNumber;\n    75→  }\n    76→\n    77→  public void setVoyageNumber(String value) {\n    78→    this.voyageNumber = value;\n    79→  }\n    80→}\n    81→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"e06226c2-51bc-464e-bbff-88e90e410548"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017re4B6GRxuyLiwxrrboSvm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.rest;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import javax.ejb.Stateless;\n     5→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     6→import javax.validation.Valid;\n     7→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     8→import javax.ws.rs.Consumes;\n     9→import javax.ws.rs.POST;\n    10→import javax.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n    18→\n    19→/**\n    20→ * This REST end-point implementation performs basic validation and parsing of incoming data, and in\n    21→ * case of a valid registration attempt, sends an asynchronous message with the information to the\n    22→ * handling event registration system for proper registration.\n    23→ */\n    24→@Stateless\n    25→@Path(\"/handling\")\n    26→public class HandlingReportService {\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    29→\n    30→  @POST\n    31→  @Path(\"/reports\")\n    32→  @Consumes({\"application/json\", \"application/xml\"})\n    33→  public void submitReport(\n    34→      @NotNull(message = \"Missing handling report.\") @Valid HandlingReport handlingReport) {\n    35→    LocalDateTime completionTime = DateConverter.toDateTime(handlingReport.getCompletionTime());\n    36→    VoyageNumber voyageNumber = null;\n    37→\n    38→    if (handlingReport.getVoyageNumber() != null) {\n    39→      voyageNumber = new VoyageNumber(handlingReport.getVoyageNumber());\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    HandlingEvent.Type type = HandlingEvent.Type.valueOf(handlingReport.getEventType());\n    43→    UnLocode unLocode = new UnLocode(handlingReport.getUnLocode());\n    44→\n    45→    TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(handlingReport.getTrackingId());\n    46→\n    47→    HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt =\n    48→        new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n    49→            LocalDateTime.now(), completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, type, unLocode);\n    50→\n    51→    applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n    52→  }\n    53→}\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G9G4HHuCkBpsALA8jLgkdn","session_id":"300f1a06-b6cf-43f1-b117-9879dd779de7","uuid":"fa1058fc-b227-48fa-8caa-aaba5b48f3fb"}
